title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 12-cup muffin tin. Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, baking soda and spices.
Quickly stir together both mixtures.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Fill prepared muffin cups two-thirds full and bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
To test doneness, use a sharp knife or broom straw.
When the knife or straw comes out clean, muffins are done.
Remove from oven and let them cool before removing.
Serve warm with butter or honey butter.

title: beef stew
directions: In a small pot, bring water to boil and add "beef" and soup. Reduce heat to simmer and cook until all water is absorbed.
In a large pot, heat oil and simmer garlic until it starts to brown. Add flour and stir until flour is medium brown.
Add water slowly, stirring or whisking continuously, until smooth.
Add quartered onion, large chunk potatoes, 1-inch length carrots, seasoning and gravy (optional).
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Takes about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: biddy on a bun
directions: Butter one bun, divided in half.
Place tuna spread on opened faced bun.
Broil until cheese melts and heated through.
Serve with a tossed salad.
Makes a nice lunch.
Serves 4.
Double recipe for more servings.

title: queen of bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, butter and lemon rind.
Pour mixture over eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and bread crumbs. Place ingredients in buttered baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° until firm.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: green beans casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking bowl.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place roll dough in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Saute onion in skillet.
Add sausage and a few dashes
of red pepper to taste.
Cook until sausage is done.
Drain excess grease and place sausage mixture over roll dough.
Beat eggs, milk, soup and mustard; pour over sausage mixture.
Cover with cheese. Sprinkle a little parsley and paprika on top.
May be refrigerated overnight.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Make gravy with cornstarch; add water and turkey broth.
In a pan or casserole dish, put turkey and vegetables as desired.
Pour gravy over turkey and vegetables.
Make biscuits and place over mixture.
Bake at 375° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Place Ritz crackers on cookie sheet.
Top with 1/4 teaspoon Pizza Quick sauce, 1 slice pepperoni and enough cheese to cover pepperoni when melted.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: coconut pudding pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Prepare dessert topping mix as directed on package.
Fold in pudding and 1 cup of the coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill at least 2 hours or until set.
Stir in orange juice with jam.
Serve with pie as topping.

title: crushed pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in pint jars and seal at once.
Makes 9 pints.

title: chewy pecan bars
directions: Mix together eggs, margarine, vanilla and brown sugar.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add pecans and stir to mix. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares to serve.
Do not overcook.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put a large (about 5 lb.) hen in stew pot and half cover with water.
Add a medium size onion, a few celery leaves, carrot and bay leaves.
Cook slowly until tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Add a rib of celery, finely diced, and 2 grated hard-boiled eggs.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Moisten mayonnaise with a little sweet pickle juice and fold into chicken mixture.

title: kitchen klatter sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate overnight to cut or may be rolled in balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° until done.
I get 7 1/2 dozen cookies from this recipe.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Drain tuna.
Heat milk and flour in double boiler until thick like dough.
Add tuna and onion to flour mixture.
Roll tuna mixture by tablespoons in flour and cook in skillet.

title: banana pudding
directions: Peel and slice bananas and layer with vanilla wafers in a large bowl.
Mix pudding mix, cold milk and condensed milk with mixer until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over wafer-banana layers and chill.

title: persimmon and date pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: pear and cherry salad
directions: Place the pear halves on crisp lettuce leaves.
Stone the cherries and arrange them around the pear halves.
Serve with preferred dressing.

title: layered jello salad
directions: First layer:
1 box of red, lemon or lime Jell-O, mixed according to package directions.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.

title: country lemon jello
directions: Drain pears and keep juice.
Put pears in blender and blend. Add cream cheese and blend.
Add water to the pear juice to make 2 cups and bring to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice-water mixture.
Pour into blender with pear and cream mixture.
Blend well.
Put into bowl and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan and refrigerate until set.

title: fariinisokeri kakku(finnish brown sugar cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. In bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat on low speed until moistened, then beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until top springs back.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Serve with no frosting, or serve with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: party pizza's
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet and drain well.
In a double boiler, melt cheese.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir in drained sausage.
Spread this on the miniature 1 pound loaf of rye bread. When ready to serve, place little pizzas on a cookie sheet and heat until cheese is soft.

title: white chili
directions: Heat oil in 4 quart Dutch oven.
Over medium heat, cook onions and garlic in oil, stirring occasionally until onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chicken.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken; simmer until hot.	Makes 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, celery and onion with just enough water to cook.
Cook until fork-tender.
Set aside.
Melt oleo in pan; add flour and when very well mixed, add milk gradually, stirring all the time, until the mixture begins to thicken.
Add to potatoes and stir lightly until you have a thickened soup.
You may add salt and pepper or celery salt or seed or oleo for more seasoning.
You might enjoy garlic flavored croutons or bites of Cheddar cheese on the top of your bowl of soup.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot.
Cook until it changes color.
Fill jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat Wesson Oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time while beating.
Mix cocoa, vinegar and food coloring in a small bowl or cup.
Mix in flour and buttermilk; add salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Bake in 325 degree oven for 35-45 minutes.

title: pasta with sausage sauce
directions: Cook pasta until firm, but tender; drain and toss with 1 teaspoon oil.
Cover and set aside.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Top with the sour cream.
Top with the Mozzarella cheese.
Top with crescent rolls.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana blueberry bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Stir in bananas. Add oats, nuts, flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well with banana mixture.
Add blueberries; stir until moist.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: yams and apples
directions: Toss apples and nuts with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of apples and yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pat with margarine.
Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and bake until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes. Add sugar; mix well and spread in a buttered baking dish. Mix oleo, flour, pecans and brown sugar. Mix well and spread on top of sweet potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crust is brown and glazy.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Gradually stir at least half of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Stir into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, lemon peel, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into pie shell.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and arrange in casserole dish.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces and put on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and then bread crumbs.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake with top on at 350° until bubbly and hot.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water: don't overcook.
Rinse in cold water after draining off the cooked water first.
Cut up the 6 boiled eggs.
Chop up the green onions and green peppers and add to the macaroni.
Now smooth in the real mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla.
Stir in salt and flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 425° for about 5 to 7 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and buttermilk. Thicker dough makes thicker cakes.
Makes about 9 cakes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Be sure and remove skin.
Soak chicken in broth overnight, removing all fat next day.
Use for each chicken, one can of soup after removing from broth and place in a large Pyrex dish.
Add enough broth with soup to be juicy but not too soupy (top with this).

title: sprinkled apple
directions: Clean apples and insert wooden sticks into the center of each apple at the stem end. Place on a sheet of wax paper.

Place white chocolate morsels in a microwave safe bowl. Microwave on medium power in 40 second intervals, stirring between each interval, until chocolate is thoroughly melted. Spoon melted chocolate onto the apple to coat thoroughly. Gently press sprinkles into the chocolate until the apple is thoroughly coated.

title: grape-nuts quickie
directions: Make pudding.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill for 8 hours.
Yummy!

title: beef jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into plastic bag.
Tightly close bag.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 125°.
Remove meat from bag and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 4 to 8 hours, until done.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Put in pan.
Beat together egg and milk.
Pour over noodles.
Brown hamburger; add spaghetti sauce.
Layer over noodles.
Sprinkle cheese over hamburger.
Spread pepperoni over cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Serve with platters of cleaned vegetables for dipping.

title: copper pennies
directions: Into a large bowl, place carrots, pepper and onion in layers. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix tomato soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over carrots and cover tightly.
Refrigerate 12 hours (if possible).
Serve as a vegetable or salad.
The drained extra dressing is good on a tossed salad.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain juice from 1 jar artichokes into a skillet. Saute the onion and garlic in the juice. Drain the other jar and chop all artichokes.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, then add the bread crumbs, Tabasco sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stir in the onion, garlic, cheese and artichokes.
Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: moms meat loaf
directions: Add beaten eggs to the ground beef and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except the bacon- mix well.
Line a loaf pan with bacon slices and press meat mixture into pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and oil and beat until creamy.
Add pineapple (less the 6 tablespoons of juice) and vanilla.
Mix. Then add shredded zucchini (unpeeled and patted between paper towels to remove excess water).
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Very good and no icing needed.

title: easy popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello, kool aid, and sugar into the boiling water. Add in the cold water.
Put into molds or ice cube trays and freeze.
Great summer treats.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water, then add 1/2 cup cold water. Cool to room temperature.

title: scottish rich cream scones
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar in a large bowl. Cut in butter with a pastry blender or rub in with fingertips. Mix in egg and cream with a fork.
Stir in raisins.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board and pat out in a circle about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut in wedges.
Brush tops with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes. Makes 12.
Eat while hot.

title: company broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli per directions but cook only 4 minutes. Drain; place in 2-quart baking dish.
Add nuts, combine soup, milk and cheese and pour over other ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.
When removed from oven, sprinkle with onions.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: To make the crust, mix crumbs, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into bottom of 9 inch spring form pan. Beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, vanilla and eggs. Pour over crust, Bake at 350° for 55 - 65 minutes. Cool overnight before removing from pan.

title: one hour no-hands bread
directions: First,
preheat flour and wheat germ in 350° oven for 10 minutes in small bowl of electric mixer (so flour won't cool when it's transferred to another bowl).
Add liquid ingredients from blender to dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix at lowest speed two minutes.
You'll notice the change in the dough as the gluten develops.
It gets stringy and may wind around the beaters. Scrape the dough from the beaters and bowl into a buttered pan, 9 x 4 x 3-inch.
Place pan on back burner of electric range (where heat from oven is vented) to rise for 10 minutes.
The pan of dough may be placed in a pan of warm water or in a warm place to rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or so.

title: dark chocolate sauce
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan. Gradually stir in corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or chilled over ice milk, nonfat frozen yogurt or angel food cake.
Yields 1 cup.

title: chile rellenos bake
directions: In large skillet, crumble together beef, sausage, onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until meat is browned; drain.
Line 9-inch by 13-inch baking dish with half of the chiles; top with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add meat mixture, top with remaining chiles; set aside.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Mix melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place other ingredients (in order listed) on top of cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: apple pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hot and spicy wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse chicken.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and garlic salt.
Roast, covered, in oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover, add 5 ounces hot sauce and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 5 ounces of Tabasco sauce over wings and keep warm until ready to serve.
Wings may be brushed with a tablespoon of margarine prior to and during roasting.
Serves 5.

title: mini monte cristo sandwiches
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons butter and mustard; evenly spread on bread.
Top with cheese, ham and remaining bread (buttered side down).
Cut each into 4 triangles.
Beat eggs, milk and soup mix. Dip sandwiches in egg mixture.
Coat well.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Cook sandwiches until golden.

title: broccoli casserole 3
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain well and chop. Melt margarine and add soup and onion.
Heat until well mixed. Put broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour heated mixture over broccoli. Spread layer of cheese, then sprinkle stuffing on top and cover.
Cook at 350° for approximately 20
minutes.

title: peanut butter clay(edible)
directions: Mix in medium size bowl until the dough is smooth.
Let your kids form the mixture into shapes, animals, etc.
They can be decorated with peanuts, raisins, chocolate chips, coconut, etc.

title: easy-d-fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Stir constantly, about 5 minutes, over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Mix ingredients together and freeze until time to serve.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add zucchini.
Mix and stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into two 5 x 7-inch loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Combine the first 11 ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with egg slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: congealed salad with crabmeat
directions: Combine unflavored gelatin and 2 tablespoons water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine unflavored and flavored gelatin, salt and 3 cups water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.

title: chicken in french onion sauce
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine vegetables and 1/2 can onions. Arrange chicken on vegetables.
In a small bowl, combine bouillon, garlic salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and vegetables. Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes or until chicken is done. Baste chicken with pan juices and top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put rice in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Mix soups with water and pour over rice.
Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine.
Lay on top of rice.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: orange brittle
directions: Grease large cookie sheet.
Grate peel from orange; set peel aside.
Squeeze 1/4 cup juice from orange.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan with candy thermometer in place over medium heat, heat orange juice, sugar, corn syrup and salt until boiling and sugar is dissolved, stirring occasionally.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently, until temperature reaches 300° or hard-crack stage (when a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water separates into hard and brittle threads).
Remove saucepan from heat; immediately stir in reserved orange peel, butter or margarine and baking soda.
Pour at once onto cookie sheet.
With 2 forks, lift and pull mixture into rectangle about 14 x 12-inches.
Cool. Can be considered low protein.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Spread in pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from inside of pan. Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Place biscuits on top and brush with margarine.
Bake until brown.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish. Cover each piece of chicken with a slice of cheese. Combine wine and soup and pour over chicken. Sprinkle dry dressing over the top. Drizzle butter over all. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a
tube pan or two loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 70 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put half the nachos in the bottom of a casserole dish. Sprinkle with half the onions. Combine chili and water; pour half over the casserole. Top with half the cheese, then repeat. Put in 400° oven until bubbly.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, almonds, citron, orange peel, cherries and vanilla.
Combine eggs and sugar, then add to cheese mixture, stirring until blended.
Roll 2/3 of dough between 2 floured sheets of waxed paper in a circle to fit a 9-inch loose-bottom cake pan or 10-inch pie plate.
Fit rolled dough in pan.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Roll remaining dough; cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange strips in lattice pattern on top of filling; crimp edges.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until lightly browned and crust is golden.
Cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Heat oil slightly (medium). Sift flour and mix with all but 4 tablespoons of buttermilk. Put the 4 tablespoons on top of batter and pour medium hot oil on top of buttermilk. Stir well and drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto bread pan with lip. Bake at 475° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and corn meal; mix well.
Add eggs and margarine, beating well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Put fresh raspberries into a bottle.
Fill with vinegar and let stand 1 week.
It will turn red and ready to serve.

title: incredible quiche
directions: Combine the bacon, cheese and onion and sprinkle over a large buttered pie plate or quiche dish.
Place the milk, biscuit mix, eggs and seasoning into a blender and blend well.
Pour this mixture into the dish over the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until quiche is golden brown.

title: mushroom paprika soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, oleo and paprika.
Sprinkle in flour and parsley.
Add beef broth and simmer.
Mix together egg yolk and sour cream.
Slowly add to soup and heat.
Do not boil!!

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Slowly add milk.
Blend in Cool Whip and pour into prepared crust.
Top with nuts.
Freeze until firm; takes 4 to 6 hours.
Cover with plastic wrap if any leftover in freezer.

title: date-nut cream cheese loaf
directions: In small bowl, place chopped dates and boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Beat eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add date mixture.
Add flour mixture.
Cut cream cheese into 3/4 inch cubes.
Fold in. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake 70 to 75 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Refrigerate when completely cool.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm. Combine in bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour until dough is stiff, add gradually.
Knead dough for approximately 5 minutes, then cover. Let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until light and doubled in size, 50 to 60 minutes.
Then stir down.
Place in greased bread pan.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles 20 minutes.
Set aside a small bowl of sauce.
Grease a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2 casserole.
Arrange in the following order:

2 or 3 spoons (very thin layer) layer of sauce in bottom of dish; 3 noodles; cover with mozzarella, ricotta and parmesan cheese in that order; sauce, 3 noodles; cheese; sauce; 3 noodles; cheese; sauce and noodles.
This is the top layer of noodles, cover this with the sauce that was set aside.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes if cooked immediately.
If refrigerated bake for 1 hour.

title: red pepper burchett
directions: Mix together red peppers, tomatoes and purple onion; set aside. Mix vinegar, 2 tablespoons olive oil, salt, pepper and sugar. Pour over pepper mixture. Toss and chill. Slice baguette. Brush bread with 1/4 cup olive oil. Bake at 400° for 4 minutes. Spoon tomato mixture on top. Place Feta cheese on top. Broil 3 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apple salad
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold cooked sauce into Cool Whip.
Combine fruits and nuts; add sauce to fruits and nuts. Keep cool until served.
Serves 6.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend 1st five ingredients and spread on muffin halves.
Cut each half into quarters (makes 48 pieces).
Freeze for 24 hours. (Great for making ahead of time for guests.) Broil for 5 minutes, until light golden brown.
(Can go from freezer to broiler.)

title: white russian cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve garnished with additional whipped cream flavored with Kahlua, if desired.

title: chow funn noodles
directions: Saute meat in oil until pink is gone.
Add stir-fry vegetables. Cook until tender.
Add cooked noodles, season with salt and pepper and shoyu.
Add optional vegetables, simmer until vegetables are heated.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Add melted butter to sugar and cream well. Add eggs one at a time. Stir in vanilla and pecans. Layer bottom of unbaked pie shell with chocolate chips and cover with pie filling. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Individual tart shells can also be used.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Let cool and make sandwiches by adding filling.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together
twice;
set aside.
Cream butter; add sugar slowly, beating constantly; cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture, 1/2
cup at a time, beating constantly.
Stir in extract.
Turn batter in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in
preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake
test done.
Place cake on rack; cool completely before serving.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well (mixer at low speed) for 2 or 3 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamed herring
directions: Sprinkle onion with sugar, juice of a lemon and herring liquid.
Mix in the drained herring and sour cream.
Let stand overnight.

title: fried cabbage and macaroni
directions: Mix cabbage and salt and let stand for 30 minutes; squeeze by hand to drain off moisture.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes, or until tender.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Combine butter or margarine, sugar, pepper, caraway seed, cabbage and macaroni in large skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until lightly browned.
Add pimiento. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a deep 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Let prepared mashed potatoes cool slightly.
Stir in sour cream, eggs, chives, salt and pepper.
Spread in casserole. Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 more minutes until puffed and cheese is melted.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Simmer 1 hour after it comes to a boil.
Put in canning jars. Process in 15 minute water bath.

title: tortellini with spinach
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add spinach to garlic and mix.
Remove spinach mixture.
Add tomatoes to pan and mash with potato masher. Add spinach back into mixture.
Add to taste the white wine, grated cheese and red pepper.
Cover sauce and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over cheese tortellini.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, onion and pepper together.
Shape into ball and roll into pecans.
Chill.

title: gainor's crabbies
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
Split English muffins and spread with mixture.
At this point, they may be frozen.

title: jello delight
directions: Crush crackers.
Melt butter; put on crackers to make a crust for an 11-inch pie plate.
Save 1 cup of crackers for the top. Dissolve jello in boiled hot water.
Add sugar.
Let it stand until it cools.
Add lemon juice.
Whip Carnation milk until peaks form.
Add cool mixture; whip 1 minute more.
Pour mixture into chilled graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining cup of crumbs. Chill for 4 hours.

title: nine bean soup mix
directions: Mix and divide into 2 cup portions for use or to give as gifts.
Give with following recipe:

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Peel shrimp and cut vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Place peeled shrimp in pan and cook in oil on medium until it turns pink.
Do not overcook.
Remove shrimp.
Add all vegetables listed and stir-fry until tender.
Do not overcook vegetables.
Remove vegetables; add more oil to pan.
Add rice, stirring until golden brown.
Add water and soy sauce; let rice cook.
Do not overcook rice (follow directions on the box of rice you are using).

title: corn pone pie
directions: Heat ingredients together.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Brown sausage; drain. Crumble over bread.
Put cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add mustard and half and half.
Pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: italian pasta accents
directions: Warm olive oil and garlic in a medium skillet.
Add tomato, pepper and fresh basil.
Stir and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add Pasta Accents and water; stir to combine.
Cover; simmer 3 to 5 minutes until vegetables are crisp and tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in large 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours until brown on top.

title: schaum torte
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat whites until stiff and they hold peaks.
Thoroughly beat in 2 tablespoons sugar at a time, 3 times. Then add vanilla, vinegar and sugar* all at once.
Grease and flour 9-inch spring-form pan, then fill with 2/3 of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour.
(For kisses, grease and flour cookie sheet, then make a circle of small kisses.)
Top with whipping cream sweetened with 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and 2 to 3 drops vanilla.

title: fancy burgers
directions: Squish all ingredients together except butter.
Form nice, thick patties.
Saute in butter on low-to-medium heat until brown on the outside.
Simmer on low about 30 minutes.
Add gravy and serve with mashed potatoes or on burger buns.

title: white cherry fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes to 238° (soft ball).
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (110°), about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and hold its shape. (Requires very little beating.)
Quickly stir in nuts and cherries and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm before cutting. Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Put raw hamburger in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion.
Mix water and soups; pour over hamburger. Add 2 cans drained veggies.
Put Tater Tots on top in rows.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins and preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and stir until well moistened.
Save a small amount of the sugar and mix with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon for sprinkling on top of each muffin.
Spoon mixture into tins, about 1/3 full, and bake for 20 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in the middle.
Good hot served with butter!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients, omitting cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Pour meat over cheese, then pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut sausage into around 3-inch pieces. Quarter the potatoes and cut the onions into chunks.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour olive oil on top just covering sausage, potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle oregano on top. Do not cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2
hours, turning potatoes and sausage often to brown all sides.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oranges, oil, and eggs (mix thoroughly).
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients and spread onto cooled cake.
Serves 16 and takes about 40 minutes to make.

title: hershey pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve coffee granules in water.
In another bowl, combine flour, cocoa, salt and buttermilk to creamed mixture, beating just until mixture is blended.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 20 minutes. Remove from pan.
(Cool completely and sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.)
Best when baked 1 to 2 days prior to eating for a richer taste.

title: italian beef
directions: Salt and pepper meat that has been placed in the Dutch oven. Add bay leaf, oregano, vinegar, caraway seed and first 1/2 cup of water.
Cook slowly for three hours.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: Peel and cut zucchini like apple slices. Boil about 5 minutes. Drain. Put in cold water for 5 minutes. Drain well.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Use only upper wing sections.
Use tips for stock, if desired. Dip pieces in egg; roll in cornstarch.
Fry wings in hot oil for about 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Place on baking sheet. Season with pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes up to 4 servings.

title: chocolate cherry pound cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and water together; beat thoroughly.
Pour in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with the baking powder and salt.
Cut in the shortening until mixture has a fine, even crumb. Place in a closed container; keep in refrigerator, using as desired.
This mixture will keep at least a month in the refrigerator.
It will yield five batches with two cups of the mixture to the batch.
It may be used for biscuits, dumplings, shortcake, waffles, muffins, quick coffee cake and dozens of other things.

title: texas style lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat; drain.
Add seasoned salt, taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, sauce and chilies; mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs. In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of the meat sauce, half of the tortillas, half the cottage cheese mixture and half of the Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin pie(for diabetics)
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer bowl and mix at medium speed until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.
One serving:
30 g. carbohydrates; 9 g. protein; 16 g.
fat.

title: delicious baked potatoes
directions: Wash
potatoes.
Slice in 1-inch
slices.
Put
a
thin slice of onion and thin slice of butter
between each slice of potato. Hold potato together and
wrap
in
tinfoil.
Repeat procedure with each potato.
Lay them on a
pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: dottie's cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine sugar, yeast, salt and 2 cups flour in mixing bowl. Heat water and margarine until warm.
Add to dry ingredients in mixing bowl; beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour and 2 eggs; beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in refrigerator or use as needed.

title: tyler's tuna fish salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Serve over lettuce or toast.

title: viv's dump cake
directions: Do not grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not beat cake, but mix well.
Mix together all cake ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, mash up.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Take one cup broth and saute pepper and onions until clear.
Add to spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into large casserole.
Put in the oven until hot and bubbly.

title: heavenly hot chocolate
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, combine the skim milk, evaporated skim milk and sugar.
Heat, uncovered, over low heat until the milk bubbles gently, about 5 minutes.

title: fast pace beans n' rice
directions: Cook rice; add butter.
Combine beans and picante sauce. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: pork and acorn squash
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Trim fat from chops.
Sprinkle both sides generously with pepper, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Place on large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Put squash on top of chops.
Fill hollows with brown sugar, honey and oleo.
Put mushrooms on top of chops.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Put on baking sheet and bake about an hour or until tender.
Serves 2.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and buttermilk.
Cook in double boiler about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat egg whites very stiff; fold into cooked mixture while still hot.
Set aside to cool, then pour into 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: zip-quick dessert
directions: Pour pie filling (apple, cherry or other favorite) into 8-inch cake pan or square baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the fruit.
Cut butter stick into small pieces and dot over the cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook the rice in water.
Meanwhile, fry the bacon until crisp. Remove from fire; drain off most of the grease.
In the same frying pan, fry the scrambled eggs; remove from fire.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When done, remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cran-raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until melted.
Add undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Stir sour cream and add to jello mixture.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: hot vegetable delight
directions: Heat soup and Cheez Whiz in saucepan.
Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain.
Pour sauce into 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour vegetables over sauce.
Sprinkle onion rings on top. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley, carrot curls and cauliflower.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Boil for 3 minutes.
Add drained vegetable mixture and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, cucumbers, onion and tomato in bowl.
Blend sour cream with mayo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add sour cream mixture to corn mixture.
Chill.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips over hot water (not boiling) in double boiler. Add noddles and peanuts and toss together until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased waxed paper.
Use two spoons, one to scoop mixture out of the other.
Allow to cool and dry.
Makes about 55 to 60 crunchies.

title: hot 'n spicy sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Press 1 tube of crescent rolls on the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cream all ingredients, except egg white, together.
Pour on top of rolls.
Place the other tube of rolls on top.
Brush with egg white, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lime parfait pie
directions: In a large bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in lime peel and lime juice.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill till partially set (the consistence of unbeaten egg whites).
Whip the 1 cup whipping cream and fold into lime mixture.
Chill till mixture mounds when spooned.
Turn into baked pastry shell.
Chill several hours or overnight until set. To serve, top with unsweetened whipped cream and maraschino cherries if desired.
Cover and chill to store.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mumu's banana pudding
directions: By hand, beat sugar, flour and eggs in bowl with a little of the milk.
Heat milk to almost boiling, then add mixture to heated milk.
Continue to stir mixture and milk over heat until it thickens.
When it thickens, remove from burner and add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Layer wafers, bananas, pudding, wafers, bananas, pudding, then put wafers on top.

title: 4-h apple crisp
directions: Grease a baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) or a 2-quart baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure the oats, flour, salt, cinnamon and brown sugar into a bowl.
Remember to pack the brown sugar. Measure the margarine.
Cut it into the dry ingredients until it is like small peas.
Adjust the oven racks so that the pan is in the center of the oven.
Peel and slice the apples.
Arrange in the baking pan or dish.
Spread the oatmeal mixture on top of the apples.
Press lightly.
Bake 30 minutes until topping is light brown and the apples are tender.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in bowl.
Add pistachio pudding.
Stir, then add can of fruit cocktail.
Add marshmallows and coconut.
Mix.
Let salad sit in refrigerator until cold and serve.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Place ham and cheese on flattened chicken breast and roll up. Place rolled chicken breast into chili shell and secure with toothpick.
Place stuffed chilies into buttered baking dish.
Pour liquids over stuffed chilies and bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.
Freezes well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla and pinch of salt together; beat well.
Add apples and chopped pecans and mix well. Pour batter in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Punch holes in cake with a fork and pour Glaze over cake while cake is hot.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all together and cook in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Press mixture into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Cut into wedges and serve hot.
Serves 6 people.

title: easy banana nut cake
directions: Mash banana and add to cake mix.
Follow directions on the box and bake in a Bundt pan.
Cool.
To top with glaze:
Stir hot milk or water into confectioners sugar.
Drizzle on top of cake.

title: bess' cookies
directions: Mix egg, sugar and peanut butter together well.
Roll in 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press chocolate star in center of each cookie.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet for short while before removing.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.
Use ungreased cookie sheet for baking.

title: overnite buns
directions: Start at 1:00 p.m.
Boil water, salt and sugar for 5 minutes. Add shortening and cool.
Add flour to cooled liquid.
Add softened yeast.
Beat well.
Add eggs.
Knead for 10 minutes. Dough will be double at 6:00 p.m.
Knead down at 9:00 p.m.
Shape and put in greased pans.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, bake at 420° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix
ingredients
minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: split pea one-dish meal
directions: Put ground beef in a pan.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, rice, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and boil gently for about 25 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add split peas.
Heat slowly until hot.
Makes 2 servings, about 1 cup each.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix catsup, vinegar, onion, Worcestershire sauce and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved. Then add oil and mix again. Refrigerate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over.
Sprinkle with sugar, then cheese and bacon bits.

title: corn casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Put oil in skillet and get hot.
Slice an onion with the potatoes and place in hot oil.
Cook slowly with lid on.
Remove lid after potatoes are tender and cook, uncovered, until brown.
When potatoes have been placed in serving dish, sprinkle grated cheese and put on top of potatoes while hot. Serve.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender in plenty of water.
When done, remove hen from broth and debone.
Simmer celery, onions and bell pepper in broth until tender.
Boil spaghetti in broth and season with salt and pepper.
Dice chicken, mushrooms and pimento; add to vegetables and spaghetti.
Cube cheese and add to chicken mixture.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring oil, water and cocoa to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk and baking soda; mix well.
Add to mixture.
Beat well.

title: light crab spread
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and salt.
Finely chop onion.
Add to cream cheese mixture along with pressed garlic.
Mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bottom of small 8-inch pan.
Coarsely chop tomato and bell pepper and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Top with crab meat.
Snip parsley and sprinkle over crab meat.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve spread with bread slices.
Yield:
15 to 20 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, margarine and salt.
Combine with all ingredients except cheese and pour into large casserole (greased).
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yogurt-fruit shake(great with fresh fruit)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend about 30 seconds, or until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: ham and chili cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, deviled ham, scallions and chilies.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator to soften slightly before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 to 2 cup cheese ball.
We add a little Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce also (hot and spicy).

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add ground cumin, chili powder, garlic salt, pepper and salt.
Add 1/2 tomato sauce, 1/2 chopped chilies and 1/2 can chili to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Mixture should be thick.
Pour half of taco sauce in large dish.
Dip a tortilla in sauce.
Transfer to 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon in 1 teaspoon sour cream, some cheese and some of the meat mixture and roll with seam-side down.
Continue doing this until all tortillas have been used and dish is full.
Heat remaining portions of can of chili with tomato sauce added.
If you have some mixture remaining also add this to chili.
Spoon onto top of enchiladas.
Top with shredded cheese and bake 45 minutes, uncovered, in 350°
oven.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Pour oil in pan.
Add garlic and lightly brown.
Add shrimp and cook until translucent.
Remove shrimp and discard oil.
Add butter and parsley to pan.
Add white wine and lemon juice.
Add fresh parsley.
Reduce liquid and pour over shrimp.

title: original new york cheese cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly with a mixer.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: hungry man's soup
directions: Add first 6 ingredients in large pan and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add cooked and drained hamburger and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for at least one hour.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook pasta; set aside.
Drain fruits and save juices (for cooked dressing).
Cook sugar, flour, salt, egg and fruit juice until thick.
Mix all together with marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: biscotto di regina
directions: Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Sift together in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in with pastry cutter or two knives until pieces are size of small pea the shortening. Stir to make a soft dough.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs (2 at a time; beat after each addition).
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream; beat.
Add the rest of flour and sour cream; beat.
Add soda, baking powder and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Can use a preheated or cold oven.

title: nut snackers
directions: Toast walnut halves and almonds with salt in 15 x 10 x 1-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan in 325° oven 10 to 15 minutes until light brown. Remove from pan.
Melt butter in pan.
Combine egg whites with sugar, vanilla and flour.
Fold in toasted nuts.
Spread in buttered pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally to break apart until brown.
After baking, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve as cookie or candy.

title: savory stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, brown and cook onion until done. Pour off drippings.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice steak sauce and pepper; set aside.
Cut tops off peppers; remove seeds.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers; arrange in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until peppers are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wine cake
directions: Blend and beat cake mix, oil, wine, eggs, pudding and nutmeg for about 5 minutes.
Bake in 10-inch greased tube pan at 350 degrees for about 45 mins. or until it springs back when touched lightly.
When cool sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: frosty
directions: Mix the two milks together with mixer. Add the Cool Whip and vanilla. Continue mixing until well blended. Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: honey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs and honey together.
Add sugar and mix again.
Mix coffee with baking powder, and then add with margarine to the egg mixture.
Add baking soda, flour, cinnamon and beat together well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 55 minutes to an hour.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and pecans on bottom.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt butter; add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well; then spread over top of cake mixture.
(Do not stir into cake.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in mashed berries and water; mix well.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Chill for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Fold in remaining berries.
Pile into pie shell and top with whipped topping.

title: squash pickle
directions: Combine vegetables and salt (1 tablespoon).
Let stand 1 hour in ice water.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; add vegetables and bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat.
Put into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: favorite fudge
directions: In saucepan, put sugars, salt, milk, oleo and marshmallow creme.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Beat until glossy; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Cool and cut into squares, before it is completely cool.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: In blender, blend green chilies, olives and onion.
Mix all ingredients, except tortillas, in a bowl.
Spread thin layer of mixture on each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Slice and serve as an appetizer.

title: quick and easy creamy broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in 5-quart pot with broccoli. Allow broccoli to come to a full boil. Add soups. Reduce heat to medium. Stir frequently. Cook until creamy consistency. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vel-rol cheese dip
directions: In microwave bowl add half of cheese, then Ro-Tel.
Microwave in 20 second increments to make sure cheese does not burn and stir with each check. Keep adding cheese until cheese is at desired dipping stage, then dip is done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Partially cook and drain vegetables.
Add margarine and soup. Pour into a buttered casserole.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Cover cheese with croutons.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: curried pork sate
directions: In bowl, stir together the soy sauce, oil, wine, sugar, curry powder and pepper flakes.
Add pork and toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, tossing occasionally. Prepare a fire in a grill.
Position the oiled grill rack 4 to 6-inches above fire.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers of zucchini, onion, tomatoes and green pepper.
Top this with the cheese slices. Cover with bread cubes and drizzle with the melted butter.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients, except margarine or butter and bread. Melt butter in skillet on medium heat.
Dip bread in egg mixture, covering both sides.
Cook until golden brown.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar and syrup.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: steamed dandelion
directions: Wash, peel and slice roots.
Prepare like carrots, cooking in small amount of water and seasoned with salt and pepper.
Drain and add small amount of butter.

title: rice-broccoli crunch
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup, milk, water chestnuts and 1/3 jar of Cheez Whiz; blend.
Stir in thawed and drained broccoli and rice.
Pour into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Soften remaining Cheez Whiz by warming over double boiler.
Spread over casserole.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Mix warm milk, yeast, sugar, shortening and 4 cups of flour. Should be like pancake mix.
Let rise 2 hours.

title: knock 'em naked
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Keep warm.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted butter in large bowl. Form into ball; split in half.
Spread 1/2 in greased and lightly floured (with cocoa) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, salt, yeast and sugar.
Add water, milk and oil and beat for 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make kneadable dough and knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Divide into loaves.
Let rise until no more than doubled.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked rotini
directions: Cook and drain rotini noodles.
Brown and drain hamburger meat. Add Italian seasoning, dried onion, pepperoni, and pizza sauce. Layer in pans (2 8x8 square pans).
Pour spaghetti sauce in bottom of pans.
Add noodles and hamburger mixture and then the mozzarella cheese.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts.
Refrigerate-overnight best.
Shape mixture into ball and roll over chopped nuts, covering ball completely.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Cook chicken and remove from broth.
Debone chicken and dice.
Return chicken to broth and add tomatoes, onions, celery and macaroni.
Bring to a boil; stir well.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Add milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage, crumbled.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add sausage.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Can be prepared 24 hours in advance.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all together and use on bread or serve on crackers.

title: pickled beet salad
directions: Use juice from pineapple and beets to make 1 cup of liquid. To make Jell-O, use 1 cup boiling water and the cup of juice.
Add beets, pineapple and nuts after Jell-O begins to thicken.
Serve with sour cream.

title: fat-free cobbler
directions: Mix biscuit mix, sugar and milk together.
Pour in pan sprayed with Pam nonstick spray.
Add pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 8-minute peanut brittle
directions: Butter or spray Pam on cookie sheet.
In a deep microwave dish, stir together sugar and syrup.
Cook on High (in microwave) 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter; stir.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir in soda. Pour onto cookie sheet.
Break up when cooled.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top generously with Mozzarella cheese and thin slices pepperoni.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 50 minutes.
This freezes well.
Can also be made in microwave.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown rice
and onion in margarine; put in baking dish. Pour bouillon
and
water over rice and add Italian seasoning. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Very good with meat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smoked deer
directions: Mix two parts Wicker's with one part dressing. Place deer in a Ziploc bag and cover with marinade. Remove excess air from bag and seal. Allow meat to marinate in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours, flipping bag over half way through time. Remove meat from marinade and wrap bacon around meat. Secure with toothpicks. Cook on smoker according to smoker's directions. This tastes best if not overcooked. Remove at 130° to 140° for medium rare. (I use a digital meat thermometer.)

title: fresh blueberry cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, eggs, butter, milk, salt and vanilla.
Beat well, then stir in blueberries.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until finished.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook together and drain off grease the bacon, chopped onion and ground meat.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large bowl, sift sugar and flour.
In heavy pan, combine butter, shortening, and coffee or water.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Use a wooden spoon.
Pour in well greased pan, 17 1/2 x 11-inches.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While brownies are baking, make the frosting.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: gran's cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool completely and store in tins, separated by paper doilies.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Combine oatmeal, butter, salt, brown sugar, and corn syrup. Mix well.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.
Don't over bake.
Over hot water melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over baked layer.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: orange refrigerator salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix well. Add orange and pineapple. Fold in whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix ingredients
together
day before use so flavors can blend together.
This is wonderful for the holidays.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and vanilla.
Then add to the Jell-O and water mixture prepared according to directions on Jell-O box.
Fold in whipped Pet milk.
Pour cheesecake mixture into graham cracker crust and chill in refrigerator.

title: cheese in pumpernickel shell
directions: Cut off top of pumpernickel bread.
Pull out pieces of bread until only the shell is remaining.
Leave pieces out a few hours until they get crusty.
Combine cheeses, beer and garlic.
Blend with mixer.
Fill shell with mixture and surround with bread pieces.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into three round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato cheese pie
directions: Butter well a 9-inch pie pan or casserole dish.
Line pan with bread, butter side down, cutting strips to fit around the sides. Brush bread surface with beaten egg white and sprinkle with dry bread crumbs.
Drain tomatoes from the juice.
Lay tomatoes on crumbs.
Sprinkle with the salt, pepper, sugar and onions. Sprinkle evenly with grated cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: working woman's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (I use a 9-inch pie pan).
Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with fruit, do not stir.
Sprinkle top with spice and a little sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: brown soda bread
directions: Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Rub the butter into flour mixture.
Then add enough buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly until smooth and transfer to the baking sheet.
Shape into a large round about 2 inches thick.
Using a floured handle of a wooden spoon, form a large cross on top.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 375° until risen and firm.
Cool for 5 minutes before transferring to wire rack to cool.
Makes one 2-pound loaf.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 skillets.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla together. In another bowl, mix the brown sugar and pecans.
Wash, drain and dry the grapes.
Add the cream cheese mixture to the grapes and blend well.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nut mixture over the top, but DO NOT STIR.
Refrigerate overnight and stir together just before serving.

title: b l t dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill several hours.
Serve on cocktail rye or toasted white bread and cut off crusts; cut toast diagonally into fourths.

title: parmesan corn-on-the-cob
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients.
Spread on corn.
Wrap each ear in heavy-duty plastic wrap and place on a microwave-safe plate.
Microwave at High 10 to 13 minutes, rearranging once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: marmalade cream
directions: In a small saucepan, bring sugar and water to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and refrigerate until cold.
In a large mixer bowl, gradually whisk lemon syrup into cream.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until stiff. (Lemon syrup and vanilla may be folded into small carton of Cool Whip.)
Fold in orange marmalade.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl until lemon-colored.
Add oranges.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add to orange mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes at low speed of electric mixer or until tiny flakes of oranges are showing.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, water, Eagle Brand milk and pudding mix. Mix well and then fold in Cool Whip (saving enough to cover top).

Using a large dish, put a layer of wafers and a layer of bananas; pour filling over this and continue until all ingredients are used. Cover top with Cool Whip and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: tomato gravy
directions: After frying tomatoes, add butter to last pan.
Add 3 or 4 slices of tomatoes.
Fry, but not very brown.
Mash.
Add a little more butter.
Add about half as much flour as butter. Brown a little.
Add milk to right consistency.
Add a little sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil; serve over bread. Makes one serving.

title: fried wonton
directions: In a bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.

Place about 1 teaspoon of meat mixture in the center of the wonton skin, fold over, bring the two corners around in shape of wonton and press corners of the wrapper together (seal with the egg yolk and water mixture).
Fry in hot oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with "Sweet and Sour Sauce".

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Over medium heat in hot butter/margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender (chicken and broccoli); stir occasionally.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the cocoa, water, honey, sugar, orange peel and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 2 minutes, or until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk; heat just until simmering.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into 6 cups.
Serve with cinnamon stick stirrers, if desired. Makes 4 cups, 6 servings.

title: chilled lemon pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs, margarine and sugar; press onto bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 8 minutes. Cool.

title: taco ritos
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and pepper; drain fat. Add chopped olives and garlic salt. Spread on flour tortillas. Add lettuce and tomato. Roll and place in shallow pan. Top with Longhorn cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Pour enchilada sauce and spaghetti sauce over and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter over low heat for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add consomme and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in individual bowls and top with croutons, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: pecan sundaes
directions: Mix, form into balls and slightly flatten with a glass.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Shake in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into fine strips and toast strips in pan at 200° for 1 hour.
Mix peanut butter and oil over low heat. Dip strips into peanut mixture.
Roll them in corn flake crumbs. Place on wax paper. Makes 60 sticks. Freezes well.

title: margaret's prize popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling and add cream of tartar.
Boil to soft crack stage (275° to 280°). Remove from heat and add butter, soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and form into balls.
Food coloring may be added, a few drops with vanilla.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350. In large mixing bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth. Add biscuit mix; mix well. Chill at least one hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased baking pan. Flatten with fork. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool, store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt together into double boiler.
Add butter and hot water, stirring well.
Add the juice from the lemon and grated rind from the lemon.
Cool until thickened.
Just before you take off the heat put in beaten egg yolks.
Mix well. Pour into baked pie shell in 9-inch pie pan.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Spray bottom of glass baking dish with oil. Line bottom of dish with slices of dried beef.

Roll each chicken breast and wrap a strip of bacon around the breast; fasten with a toothpick. Place on the dried beef. Mix together the sour cream and undiluted soup. Place evenly over chicken; cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours. Remove cover and bake an additional hour. Serve hot with rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham sandwich
directions: Use desired portions of ham and cheese.

title: typically texas fried cactus pad tidbits
directions: Using paring knife, remove spiny needles from cactus pads. Slice into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Wash thoroughly and drain.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; set aside.
Blend milk and eggs well.
In another bowl, mix crumbs, crackers, chili powder, cayenne and salt.
Dredge cactus in seasoned flour, then place in egg-milk mixture, then in seasoned crumbs.
Heat oil to 350°.
Fry pads in batches 1 to 2 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 40 strips.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Brown patties.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with a slice of Mozzarella cheese on each patty.
In skillet heat tomatoes and oregano.
Pour hot over meat and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with cooked spaghetti tossed with butter.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Combine wine and oil in large bowl.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and thyme.
Place chicken in mixture for at least one hour. Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Broil chicken on both sides in oven or on barbecue grill for 35 to 40 minutes. Meanwhile, combine 2 tablespoons of reserved marinade, dry mustard and honey.
When chicken is just done, brush with honey-mustard sauce and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers.
Remove stems and seeds.

Wash and drain. Combine meat, onions, salt, pepper, boiled rice, egg and 1/2 can tomato soup; mix well. Stuff peppers with this mixture. Place stuffed peppers in covered saucepan. Add rest of tomato soup with enough water to have 1 1/2-inches in the pan.
Simmer 30 minutes or until meat is cooked.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, eggs, butter and salt. Stuff into cooked shells. Pour a thin layer of tomato sauce in a shallow baking dish and put manicotti on top. Spoon rest of tomato sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil, debone and cut up chicken.
Boil spaghetti in broth from chicken, then drain.
Mix all other ingredients and melt in double boiler or microwave.
Stir in chicken, spaghetti, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Next, line a bowl with a layer of vanilla wafers, then put a layer of banana slices. Spoon in a layer of pudding.
Repeat until ingredients are all used up.
Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.

title: polly may's pumpkin mints
directions: Mix sugar and butter with fingers.
Add milk, cinnamon oil and food coloring; mix well.
Form into balls about the size of marbles and flatten the bottom to make pumpkins.
Use toothpicks to draw lines for sides and a clove as the stem.

title: brownie cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar and set aside.
In a large pan, mix and melt the oleo, oil, water and cocoa.
Add the eggs, vanilla, salt, buttermilk and soda.
Add the dry ingredients.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Scoop potatoes out of skins and place in large mixing bowl.
Add margarine, milk and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Put potato mixture back in skins.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Reheat in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: punch
directions: Pour liquids all together.
Slice lemons, oranges and limes. Add to punch.
Add all other ingredients.
Let set a while.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Stir into the milk.
Serves 4.

title: cuban salad
directions: Cut avocado into pieces; add pineapple.
Mix vinegar, oil, water and sugar.
Add to avocado and pineapple.
Toss well. Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into ungreased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Pie makes own crust and cuts like pie.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain all ingredients and mix together.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Add all ingredients except corn flakes.
Mix well and roll in small logs. Roll in crushed corn flakes and cut in small pieces.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in small baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and pepper in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese-onion corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.

title: shiny cookie icing
directions: Place sugar, milk and corn syrup in bowl and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Use as is for outlining.
Thin with additional corn syrup for coating or filling large areas.
This icing is great for painting on Christmas cookies.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Melt oleo in frying pan.
Slice zucchini, squash, onion and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce and pepper.

title: easy homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: That's all folks!
Mix well with wire beater and pour into gallon freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: 5 bean dish
directions: Cook ground beef until golden brown with onion and pepper. Drain well.
Pour into a slow cooker.
Add 5 cans of beans with juice.
Put in barbecue sauce and salt; cook slow for 2 hours.

title: graham, date and nut cookies
directions: Oven at 350 degrees.

title: mexican rice dish
directions: Cook the rice in the water for 15 minutes and rinse.
Mix the cooked rice with the other ingredients and bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: beef and tomato fried rice(a chinese-american stir-fry)
directions: Trim all fat from steak.
Slice into very thin strips. Marinate in mixture of soy sauce, water, sesame oil, white pepper and cornstarch for at least 1 hour before using.
Add 1 teaspoon of vegetable oil to a hot wok; add onion and steak.
Stir until cooked through, then remove.
Add another teaspoon of vegetable oil to wok.
Brown rice, then add beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Stir in peas, tomatoes, onion and steak.
Stir in ketchup and salt. (Add another dash of sesame oil, if desired.)
Serve immediately.

title: mattie's mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese and stir until slightly melted.
Add oranges and pineapple with syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Then fold in Cool Whip until small, then pour in mold or dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all together (tube pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: researchers' choco-nutties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oil, sweetener, egg replacer and banana in food processor.
Mix in flour, carob and coffee substitute.
Stir in walnuts, vanilla and salt.
Drop by teaspoons onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 18 to 20 cookies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the soft margarine, brown sugar and white sugar. Add the eggs, vanilla, soda, salt and flour.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat all ingredients and serve with sliced apples.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots; then drain.
Combine soup and milk mixture with sour cream.
Fold in drained squash, onion and carrots.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; then spoon squash mixture over this.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: *More or less cheese can be added.

title: luther's fish fry
directions: Heat several inches of oil in a deep iron skillet.
Float a wooden stick match in oil until it strikes.
When oil is ready, dredge fish in meal mix and drop in oil.
Fish floats when cooked. Remove when browned as desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the meat loaf ingredients together and form in a loaf. It is good to spray pan before putting meat in it.

title: aunt mary's hystaquita
directions: Grind the first 3 ingredients together.
Heat the next 3 ingredients until thick.
While still hot, pour over the ground ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate when cool.
Serve cold on crackers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and ground meat in separate skillets.
Drain and combine in 1 skillet.
Add all other ingredients except bread. Stir until cheese melts.
Spread on slices of rye bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets. Remove and place in freezer bags.
Bake when ready to use at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except macaroni and egg, in a large bowl. Add macaroni and egg.
Mix lightly.
Chill before serving.
Makes 8 servings.
