title: green tomato relish
directions: Simmer for 3 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: deedie's hamburger dish
directions: Place layer of uncooked hamburger meat in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with A.1. meat sauce or Worcestershire.
Cover meat with layer of American cheese slices or grated cheese.
Pour celery soup over cheese or mushroom soup. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
If you want more gravy, just add 2 cans of soup.
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom soup

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Mix with onion, celery, dry rice, chicken soup, mushroom soup, water and soy sauce.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Cover and bake 1/2 hour more. Serves 8.

title: stuffed lamb roast
directions: In a small saucepan, cook onions, celery and garlic in hot cooking oil until tender but not brown.
In large bowl, combine eggs, spinach, parsley, basil, marjoram and pepper.
Add onion mixture.
Stir in croutons and Parmesan cheese.
Drizzle with water to moisten, tossing lightly.
Set aside.
Pound lamb to an even thickness and sprinkle with rosemary.
Spread stuffing over lamb.
Roll up and tie securely.
Place lamb, seam side down, in a rack or in a large shallow roasting pan. Roast in a 325° oven, uncovered, using a meat thermometer, until it registers 150°.
Let roast stand for 15 minutes before carving.

title: aunt josie's cravable corn souffle
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into a souffle dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: baked jack corn
directions: Mix all except Cheddar cheese.
Pour in greased 2-quart dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and sweet milk; stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip to pudding and stir until blended.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Makes 3 layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: sausage bites (small)
directions: Heat together cheese and sausage in sauce pan.
Stir with wooden spoon until cheese is melted.
Stir in 3 cups of flour until smooth.
Cool, then chill for about 1 hour.
Form into balls about the size of a nickel.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400 for 8-10 minutes.
Remove and drain.

title: wimpie burgers
directions: Brown onions; add meat and brown.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer on stove top for several hours, the longer the better.
Add more water while cooking if dry.
Serve on hot buns.

title: ruck-a-muck
directions: Cube Spam and fry in pan until brown (no grease).
Add pineapple, peaches and green pepper.
Cook until bubbly and pineapple is just beginning to brown on edges.
Serve on rice. Serves 4.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Bring to soft boil and add vanilla.
Pour onto greased pan.

title: spicy tennessee chili
directions: Heat oil until hot; add onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add ground beef; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Add tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low. Cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring in beans.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: honey granola
directions: Combine oats, coconut, wheat germ and cinnamon in a large bowl. Combine honey, vegetable oil and vanilla with a wire whisk, then stir into dry ingredients.
Spread in greased large, shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, stirring often.
Cool thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Add optional ingredients as desired.
Store in cool dry place.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
soup and the 1 can milk.
Form into balls and brown in
skillet.
Pour
off
fat.
Add
the soup and enough milk to cover
balls.
Simmer
to
hour, uncovered.
Serve over rice, noodles, mashed potatoes or alone with bread.
Quick and easy and can be made ahead and heated.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix flour and milk with creamed mixture.
Add flavorings and baking powder.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and place in a cold oven. Turn heat to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour bag of Tater Tots on top of meat.
Mix soups and sour cream together and spread over Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cheese should be spread on top the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and let set 24 hours.
Good with vegetables.

title: pickled veggies(for the fridge)
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, sugar and celery seed in pan and bring to a boil. Add vegetables and pepper flakes and cook for 3 minutes. Cool. Place in jars and store in refrigerator. Ready to eat in a few hours.

title: baked mashed potato duo
directions: Cut baking potatoes into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Boil over high heat.
Cut sweet potatoes into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Add to baking potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer until done.
Heat milk and butter until just warm.
Remove from heat.
Mash potatoes; add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Add egg to potato mixture.
Spoon into greased dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until lightly browned.

title: west texas venison bake
directions: Cut venison into serving pieces.
Put in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Shake venison in bag and brown in oil.
Place in crock-pot.
In same oil, saute celery and onion rings.
Add to crock-pot.
Cover with tomatoes.
Use more if needed.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook on high for 4 hours or more. Or may bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over wide noodles.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add other ingredients except soda and vinegar.
Beat for 2 minutes, then fold in soda and vinegar mixture.
Do not beat after adding these.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until cake tests done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup.
Pour into a shallow casserole.
Top with onions. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Pour over crust and
sprinkle
cup
pecans over top. Bake at 340° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set.

title: stove top casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put Stove Top in a casserole dish.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Top with the soup.
Bake, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "sugar-free" date cake squares
directions: Combine water, dates, prunes and raisins in saucepan. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until fruit is tender and water is absorbed. Remove from heat. Add oleo. Stir until melted. Cool.

title: custard ice cream
directions: Heat milk in top of double boiler; do not boil.
Stir in sugar. Beat eggs with salt; blend in a little of the hot milk mixture. Add to remaining milk and continue cooking, stirring constantly, until smooth and creamy.
Strain if necessary.
Pour in mixing bowl; add cream and vanilla.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: tomato soup
directions: Fry onion in butter.
Boil tomatoes, fried onion and green pepper in the water until soft.
Add the cornstarch.
Strain and rub through a colander.
Add sugar and salt.
This may be put up in glass jars.
The recipe may be varied by omitting 2 quarts of water and diluting with milk to taste.
You may also add one-half stalk of celery at the beginning.
If so, then reduce the cornstarch to 8 tablespoons.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Brown cutlets in oil.
Mix all other ingredients together except grapes and pour over chicken.
Bake chicken for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add grapes and bake 5 minutes more.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients; pour in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix in blender.
For a stronger flavor, add more dressing.

title: teriyaki-style chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.

title: duncan hines yellow deluxe ii
directions: Mix apples, pineapple, flour and sugar and put in baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Chop up butter on top.
Spread with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over mixture of flour and sugar.
Mix well and then add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and chill.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in molasses and egg. Sift together dry ingredients. Stir in molasses mixture and blend. Roll out
1/8-inch thick and cut desired shapes. Bake cookies at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower, onion, pepper and Cheddar cheese. Mix Hidden Valley dressing according to package directions.
Mix all together.
Place in Tupperware and refrigerate.

title: pear brandy cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add oil, brandy, vanilla and eggs.
With spoon, stir until well blended.
(Mixture will be very thick.)
Fold in pears and pecans.
Pour and spread batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.

title: 7-layer bar cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt a stick of butter and add vanilla. Stir together.
On top of that, sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs, then layer in the following order: coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, dribble on the condensed milk and chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
May be frozen.

title: ann's peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts in a 2-quart microwaveproof bowl.
Cook on High in microwave for 5 minutes, then stir.
Cook on High 13 to 15 minutes, until 300° on candy thermometer. Stir in butter, soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Spread.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add cocoa and red food color; mix well.
Add flour and buttermilk; mix well.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl.
Add to batter and blend well.
Bake in 3 eight-inch or standard cake pans at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; cook 2 minutes.
Add milk. Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Beat in confectioners sugar.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: linda's casserole(breakfast dish)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together; set aside.
Place bread slices on bottom of pan.
Put cooked sausage on top of bread, cheese on top of sausage and green chilies on top of cheese.
Pour eggs and milk mixture on top of all.
Bake until done, about 45 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Form into patties.
Fry on both sides. Serve hot.

title: chow-mein sandwiches
directions: Heat chow mein in a saucepan until hot. Split rolls in half and spoon chow mein on bun. Sprinkle with crushed noodles. Garnish to taste with soy sauce and mustard. Cover buns with tops and enjoy!

title: frozen corn
directions: Heat on stove until good and hot.
Put in container and let it get cold before you put in freezer.

title: toasted nuts
directions: Soak nuts in salty water 1 hour. Drain and dry. Bake at 250°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Combine cabbage and apples. In a heavy saucepan melt butter, sugar, and vinegar. Stir in apples and cabbage. Cook on low until tender. Season with salt and pepper.

title: methodist men grits recipe
directions: Buy 16 oz. box of instant grits.

title: sweet and spicy popcorn
directions: Place sugar, chili powder, cinnamon, salt and cayenne pepper in a zip-type plastic bag or other 2-quart airtight container. Mix.
Add popcorn.
Spray popcorn with nonstick cooking spray. Close bag and shake.
Repeat one or two times until popcorn is coated.
Yields 6 cups.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: In a covered saucepan, boil sweet potatoes in a little water until tender.
Let cool.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in oblong baking dish, which has been covered with a crust.
Sprinkle sugar, ginger and water over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Roll out another crust and place on top, making slits so that steam can escape.
Bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown on top, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fish batter
directions: Combine flour, salt, cornstarch and soda; mix well.
Add water and egg; mix.
Dip dry fish into batter to coat well.
Deep fry in hot oil.

title: make your own "cream of" soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To make 1 can of soup, combine 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 1/4 cups water in a small saucepan.
Cook and stir until thick. Add celery, mushrooms, etc. for the type of soup you are substituting.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water until dissolved.
Add flour (additional flour may be added) to make dough soft.
Knead lightly.
Roll and cut out or pinch off; butter and let rise.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Add remaining ingredients, except crackers, margarine and almonds. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter and Crisco shortening thoroughly.
Add sugar a little bit at a time, creaming well after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add sifted flour mixture and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add lemon and vanilla flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over broccoli.
Add some cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place 1 teaspoon butter in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet. Heat in oven for 5 minutes.

title: tortilla chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 items in bowl. Add chilies and tortillas.
Let soak for 1/2 hour.
Spoon mixture into large shallow casserole. Cover with chicken and top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Place slightly beaten eggs in 2-quart saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup lemon juice, sugar, oleo and marshmallows.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows dissolve.
Cool.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon lemon juice over banana slices.
Add bananas, pineapple, cherries and pecans to cooked mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and pour in 3 1/2-quart mold or pan.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate, then spread cocktail sauce over the cream cheese.
Top with salad shrimp and cheese.

title: theresa's curry dip
directions: Mix together well.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Serve with raw vegetable strips.
Keeps indefinitely.
Makes 1 cup.

title: frosted caramel squares
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Spread 1/4-inch thick on flat, greased pan.
Beat egg whites with brown sugar until stiff.
Spread on top and bake in 350° oven until top turns lightly brown.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil.
Add broccoli and cook until tender.
Drain off excess oil.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef and brown lightly.
Drain off excess fat.
Add all ingredients and simmer covered for 30 minutes.

title: bubble bread(frozen bread)
directions: Leave frozen bread out 1 hour.
Cut each loaf into 16 pieces. Mix the sugar, pudding mix and melted oleo.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam and grease well with shortening.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts in pan.
Roll each piece of bread in topping mixture and put in pan.
Pour balance of mixture on top.
Let rise until double. Bake at 350°.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Put butter in a bowl and let stand until soft.
Beat well. Add sugar and mix well.
Add water, vanilla and cocoa and mix. Add oats and mix well.
Shape into 36 balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Store cookies in the refrigerator.

title: luscious layer bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll
pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine, sour cream
and
eggs
at
low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at
highest speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at
350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Center will not be firm to touch.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together with exception of cheese; put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or can use 2 casseroles and freeze one. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for about 50 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese. Drop onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian sloppy subs
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine sausage, onion and green pepper. Cover.
Microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink, stirring several times to break apart.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, catsup and Italian seasoning.
Microwave at High for 2 to 4 minutes, or until mixture is hot and flavors are blended, stirring once.
Set aside.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute ground chuck, peppers and onion; drain.
Add soup.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices and then Tater Tots. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler; set aside to cool. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and butter with an electric mixer until smooth.
On low speed, blend in melted chocolate.
Fold in whipped topping until blended.
Spoon into crust.
Cover and chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Work in shortening with fingers.
Add milk gradually.
Roll out dough on floured board.
Cut into squares and place pared and quartered apples on each.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pinch edges of dough together to form dumplings.
Place in baking dish.
Cover all with syrup made from sugar, water and butter simmered together.
Bake for 30 minutes in moderate 350° oven.
Baste dumplings during baking.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spread in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for one hours.

title: chicken tofu
directions: Brown chicken with 1 tablespoon oil. Add sugar, salt, water and shoyu. Simmer until chicken is tender (30 minutes). Add green onions and tofu. Flip the pot in upward movement (with lid) to mix.
Yields 3 or 4 servings.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale in blender at high speed until smooth.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale. Makes 4 quarts.

title: soup stock
directions: Sprinkle salt on meat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add water; bring to boiling point.
Simmer the soup, covered, 3 hours.
Add chopped vegetables, tomatoes and green pepper and cook 1 hour longer. Strain the soup; chill it.
Remove the fat and reheat the soup. Add more seasoning, if required.
Serve the soup with chopped parsley.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Drain all the grease off.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix margarine and cheese until creamy.
Add flour and other dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples.
Simmer until thick.
Add sliced apples, cook only until apples are heated through, stirring carefully.
Cool slightly and pour into pie shell.
Moisten edges of crust with water and add top crust.
Trim off excess dough and crimp edge or press with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in hot water. Add pie filling; mix well. Add undrained pineapple. Cool and set in refrigerator. Mix cream cheese and sugar until fluffy; fold in sour cream and spread on top of Jell-O. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chinese cashew casserole
directions: Combine
chicken,
nuts,
celery,
onion,
soup, water, pepper and
1/2 noodles in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Mix lightly and sprinkle with remaining noodles.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
(Can be doubled.)

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookies and place 1 tablespoon in bottom of each cup. Pour milk and pudding in bowl and beat with whisk for 2 minutes and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and 1/2 of the cookies.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then add worms.

title: oatmeal crisp
directions: Roll up and chill overnight.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Store in refrigerator.
Use for dips and salads.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add milk; return to a boil.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Yield:
Enough to frost sides of one 2-layer cake.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, flour, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and egg yolk at once.
Add milk last.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool off for 15 minutes.

title: homemade dried onion soup mix
directions: Combine onion powder, salt and sugar in a small bowl.
Add Kitchen Bouquet and stir until seasonings are uniformly brown. Add dehydrated onion and mix thoroughly until color is even. Makes the equivalent of 1 (1.5 oz.) envelope dried soup mix.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Years ago my Daddy, Zack Fore, requested a chewy ginger cookie and I began tinkering with recipes, with Daddy as my No. 1 "taste tester".
Well, he's gone now, but I think he would really like this cookie.
I know his grandkids do!!

title: marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Separate crescent dough into 16 triangles.
Dip the marshmallows into melted margarine, then roll in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.

title: old fashion butter cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar; add egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
This makes a very stiff dough and the last addition of flour must be worked in gradually.
Form 2 rolls; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Dough keeps in refrigerator for a week.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch glass casserole with PAM.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Place rolls 1/2 inch apart in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon in saucepan stirring to mix.
Pour over rolls.
Place in cold oven overnight. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Flip over onto cookie sheet or serving platter.

title: pear dessert(fast and easy recipe)
directions: Chill pears in refrigerator until ready to make.
Place lettuce leaf on plate.
On each plate put 2 pear halves atop lettuce.
Mix together well cream cheese with salad dressing. Spoon onto center of pear halves.

title: chocolate-peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats, peanut butter and vanilla and boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered wax paper.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and milk.
Fold in sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Alternate with wafers and bananas.
Use other 1/2 of Cool Whip on top.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 small ones.

title: martha jo's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep baking dish.
Add batter of flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Beat ingredients together and pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Add at least 3 cups peaches. Distribute the fruit evenly over the batter.
Do not mix. Sprinkle over this 1 cup sugar and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Bring water to boil.
Reduce heat and cook until both are melted, stirring constantly.
Spread mixture onto a wax paper lined 15 X 10 X 1 inch jelly roll pan.
Pour melted semi sweet chocolate over mixture and swirl through with a knife.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Store in refrigerator. Yield 6 dozen.

title: cocoa-banana muffinettes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line mini muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine first six ingredients; mix well.
Add combined bananas, milk, margarine, egg whites and vanilla mixing just until moistened. Fill prepared cups almost full.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until wood pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let muffins stand a few minutes; remove from pan.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tomato soup:  theme and variations
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until light brown.
Add tomato puree and sugar.
Saute 1 minute.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Strain.
Serve as is either hot or well chilled.
Serves 6.

title: sauteed beef tips with mushrooms
directions: Saute tips, onions and mushrooms until medium rare to medium; add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine bouillon with water and cornstarch and mix together.
Simmer slowly while preparing rice. Serve on rice.

title: hot cheddar cheese balls
directions: In a medium bowl, work all ingredients together until well blended.
Knead mixture with hands until it is a smooth, even dough.
Pinch off small pieces of dough (rounded teaspoonful size) and roll into ball.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 25 appetizers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and enough milk to drop into oil by spoonfuls to form a hush puppy.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with pineapple.
Mix and if nuts used, add them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 8 1/4 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan which has been greased and floured.
When baking time is completed, loosen loaf from sides of pan with knife and turn out on cake rack to cool.

title: relish
directions: Cut corn off 12 ears of corn.
Grind the first 6 ingredients; mix together.
Add corn.
Add salt.
Let set for 2 hours.
Squeeze all juice out.
Then add to remaining ingredients.
Do not heat. Mix together.
Fill jars and seal.

title: prize winning chili
directions: Soak dried beans from 15-bean soup overnight. Simmer beans and chopped onions until soft.
Cook sausage and Italian sausage in skillet until barely done.
Chop Italian sausage into small chunks. In large pot, mix beans, sausage and all other ingredients. Cook until flavors are well mixed, but beans remain intact (perhaps one hour).
Serve with cornbread or rice.

title: cheddar bacon rounds
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, seasoning and paprika.
Fold in cheese, onions and peanuts.
Crumble bacon into mixture and stir to distribute evenly throughout mixture. Refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and pitch out all of the old maids (unpopped kernels).

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Cook over low heat for 3 hours.

title: glazed doughnut snacks
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl for glaze and set aside.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Use shrimp if you can't get crawfish.
Melt margarine in aluminum Dutch oven
(don't use ironpot as black iron pot will cause crawfish to darken).
Season crawfish tails generously with Tony's Creole seasoning or salt and pepper and paprika to margarine.
Saute crawfish tails, about 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish and set aside.

title: quick draw dip
directions: Combine chili, picante sauce and cheese in a saucepan.
Warm thoroughly over low heat, stirring frequently.
Serve warm.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: anytime brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix above ingredients until the consistency of batter.
Spread into small nonstick baking dish.

title: miriam heath's jello waldorf
directions: Combine milk
and
mayonnaise and add to Jell-O and hot water. Add chopped ingredients. Chill.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle white or yellow cake mix over that.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, eggs, sugar and butter in mixer bowl and mix at high speed to quickly blend well.
Press peanut butter into greased 9-inch square baking pan and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cover with Chocolate Frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 16 (2 x 3-inch) bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place Ritz cracker crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, enough to cover bottom.
Cook broccoli.
Do not drain.
Mix in large pieces of Velveeta cheese.
Pour over crumbs.
Pour soup over mixture.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Add a little milk around the edge.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pretzel cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cookie mix as directed.
Fold in pretzels.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: black forest cake(yields one 3-layer cake)
directions: Combine eggs, egg yolks and 2/3 cup sugar.
Beat until thick and light.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Gradually fold flour mixture into egg mixture.
Fold in vanilla.
Pour batter into three 8-inch round cake pans which are lined with a greased circle of waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until top springs back when pressed lightly with finger.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Melt butter in bowl.
Mix spaghetti and Parmesan cheese together.
Spread mixture into pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Add meat sauce; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes, then slice.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening together with both sugars.
Beat in eggs and add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda and mix with shortening and egg mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and coconut, then fold in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoons, 2 inches apart, onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix ingredients (except muffins) into a spread and smooth onto English muffin halves.
Put in freezer for at least 10 minutes. Cut in quarters and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve as an appetizer.
Delicious!

title: strufoli(italian honey balls)
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and butter.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Use the 1/2 cup for mixing as needed to make dough workable.
Let dough stand,
covered, for 1/2 hour. Cut off a handful of dough and roll out into a log shape (about as thick as your finger and 18-inches long).
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Then add other ingredients.
When this is partially set, add Cool Whip to gelatine mixture.
Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Line a four-quart mixing bowl with wax paper.
Put layer of mixture, then layer of cake until all is used.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Then turn out on cake plate.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt 3 teaspoons butter in a heavy skillet.
Add the onion and cok slowly until transparent.
Remove and set aside.
Cut the beef in 1 inch by 2 1/2 inch strips.
Turn the heat to medium-high; add the beef and cook briefly, turning brown on all sides.
Remove the beef and set aside with the onions. Add the remaining 3 tablespoons butter to the skillet.
Stir in the mushrooms, cover and cook 3 minutes.
Season with pepper and nutmeg.
Whisk the sour cream and add to the pan, but do not allow it to boil. Return the beef and onions to the pan and just heat through. Yield: 6 servings.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix well; brush on chicken and grill until done.

title: bar cheese
directions: In skillet, fry bacon until crisp, crumble when cool after frying.
Melt cheese over low heat or microwave.
Stir in horseradish, salad dressing and bacon.
Makes 5 cups.

title: special k bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup good and add peanut butter. When mixed, add 3 cups Special K. Mix good and put in square pan. Melt the butterscotch chips and milk chocolate chips. Spread over bottom mixture.

title: stansfield cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix sugar and orange juice. Grind cranberries and orange rind.
Combine all ingredients and put in a cool place to set.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Heat milk and tapioca in double boiler.
Stir often.
Beat eggs; mix eggs and sugar.
Stir egg mixture into tapioca.
Cook and stir until thick or about 15 minutes.
Let cool; add vanilla. Serve plain or with cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken.
Cook rice in broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients except potato chips; place in baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: currant nut cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk and beat well with a mixer. Add vanilla, cake flour and salt.
Dough must be stiff; chill at least 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well. Sift together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Add water and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocado.
Stir in the rest of ingredients.
If needed, store in sealed plastic container and cover surface with a thin layer of mayonnaise to prevent darkening.
Stir in mayonnaise before serving.

title: french toast
directions: Take bowl and combine eggs, nutmeg and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Dip bread into mixture.
Be sure to coat both sides. Put bread in frying pan on medium until browned.
You may use syrup or other toppings on the French toast.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in lemon rind, juice, well beaten egg yolks and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 8-inch casserole.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve cold or warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together; toss lightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add oil and vinegar to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fast and easy crab dip
directions: Split cream cheese in half to make to long skinny pieces.
(It looks fancier this way.
Otherwise, you can just spread the cheese on a plate.)
Pour cocktail sauce over the top.
It can drip down the sides.
Drain the crab really well.
Sprinkle dry crabmeat over the top.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: In a saucepan, pour three cups of water and bring to a boil; cut and slice apples.
Do not leave seed in slices or peels.
Put apple slices in boiling water; add cinnamon and sugar.
Let apples cook until tender.
Add more sugar and cinnamon if taste is not sweet.
Add more water if needed.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Stir cheese until very soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly, about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Pour once into crust.
Put can of pie filling on top with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or boil for 1 hour before baking.
Place in beanpot.

Add ingredients. Fill with water to about 1-inch above beans. Bake at 275° for about 9 to 10 minutes. Check water occasionally (may substitute 2 tablespoons cold bacon grease for salt pork). Make sure to check beans for small rocks and wash them before cooking.

title: snowballs
directions: Blend sugar with margarine that is at room temperature.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix in walnuts. Roll dough into 1/2-inch diameter balls. Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes per tray.
Shake cookies in a plastic bag with 10x sugar.

title: peach cobbler(student favorite)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Grease pan; put in peaches on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry ingredients on top; then put butter on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Use as dip for raw vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Toss butter with stuffing.
Spread half of stuffing in baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water; stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Divide mixture in half. Freeze half of juice mixture; chill remaining half.

title: grilled dill salmon
directions: Heat coals or gas grill. Place fish on 24-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Brush salmon with oil and sprinkle with pepper. Wrap foil securely around fish. Cover and grill fish 4 to 6-inches from medium heat 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Mix dill dip with milk until smooth. Serve salmon with dill sauce. Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Beat together egg, milk, 1 cup Mozzarella, 1/2 teaspoon salt and garlic powder.
Break spaghetti in 2-inch pieces; cook and drain.
Add ingredients to spaghetti.
Place in a greased 17 x 11-inch pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce on top; sprinkle with oregano.
Top with 2 cups Mozzarella and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and mix with sliced onions.
Add salt.
Mix good.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Make pickling syrup of remaining ingredients.
Have this hot.
Add drained cucumbers and onions. Reheat to boiling point; do not boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: microwave velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese and salsa in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted, cut up vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pecan sticky buns
directions: Boil and then simmer 1 minute the brown sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Pour in 9-inch pan.
Arrange pecan halves in 9-inch square pan with flat sides up in bottom of the pan.
Roll dough into a rectangle.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon and sugar mixture. Roll up tightly, pinch seam to seal.
Cut in 1 inch thick pieces. Arrange 1/2 inch apart.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes until almost doubled.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert onto large dish and leave pan on until caramel drips down.

title: strawberry cheesecake torte
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line bar pan with parchment paper. Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour into pan, spreading evenly. Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Lift cake onto a cooling rack. Cool completely. Microwave water on High 1 to 2 minutes or until boiling. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Add jam; whisk until smooth. Place cake on cutting board and remove paper. Prick cake at 1/2-inch intervals. Brush cake evenly with all but 2 tablespoons of gelatin mixture. Trim 1/4-inch around edge of cake; discard edges. Cut cake crosswise into 3 equal layers.

title: nutmeg carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water for about 15 minutes.
Drain and then add other ingredients, stirring well to blend.

title: granpa's bran brown bread
directions: Combine cereal, buttermilk, raisins, molasses and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt together, then add to bran mix.
Mix well. Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 3 hours. Stir every hour.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour; gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in rice and salt; simmer about 5 to 15 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry; heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with minced parsley or chives.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Brown beef; add salt and pepper, then add other ingredients except corn.
Bring to a boil, then simmer about 45 minutes.
Add corn; continue cooking 5 more minutes.
Heat through.
If using fresh corn, cook longer.
Add a dash of red pepper or Tabasco, if you like it hot.
Serves 6.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Package in tightly covered containers.
Makes 6 cups, enough for 32 cups of tea.
To prepare: Add 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in large covered container indefinitely.
Add 1/2 cup mix to cup.
Fill with boiling water.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine sugars, butter, egg and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add flour, soda and salt; beat well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate. Drop tablespoons of dough onto greased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove and let cool on paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in heavy 3 qt. saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt, stirring until thoroughly combined.
Blend in corn syrup. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat, until candy reaches firm ball stage (245°) about 12-15 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Spoon over pecans on buttered surface.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and blend with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Place half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients and place in dish.
Top with other half of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, orange juice, cake mix and pudding.
Pour 3/4 of this mixture into a greased tube pan.
Add chocolate syrup to remaining batter and mix.
Then pour remaining batter into tube pan and swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Don't overbake.
Cool completely before icing.

title: david's breakfast pizza
directions: Bake at 350° or simmer on the range, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
(From Amy on the Internet.)

title: chili cornbread pie
directions: Chop green onion and tomato for garnish.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned; drain.
Stir in undrained beans, tomato sauce, tomato paste and taco seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Mix biscuit mix, milk, seed and egg well and spread on bottom and up sides of dish.
Cook ground beef, pepper, onion and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes. Put in pie plate.
Top with French fried onions and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cut French bread lengthwise.
Grate cheese.
Dice onions.
Mix onions, cheese, mayonnaise and oregano together.
Spread evenly over bread and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: quiche
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Layer in pie shell, half the Mozzarella, sausage and remaining Mozzarella.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sausage and mushrooms can be used together.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix oleo and eggs together.
Mix sugar, salt, pepper and both cans of corn with oleo and egg mixture.
Add corn muffin mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cake pan cake
directions: Put dry ingredients into sifter and sift directly into ungreased cake pan (8-inch square).
Make 3 holes in dry mixture, pour cooking oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in third hole. Pour cold water over all, stirring with fork until evenly blended.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Toss blueberries with cinnamon and lemon juice; place in a greased 8-inch square baking pan. In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder; stir in milk and butter. Spoon over berries.

title: lasagna
directions: Crumble sausage and ground beef, brown and drain.
Stir in soup, tomato sauce, mushrooms, onion, seasoning mix and salt.
Mix well.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch pan: 1/3 cooked noodles, 1/3 meat mixture, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
On third layer of noodles, spread last 1/3 meat mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for 20 to 25 minutes on Roast or until hot in center.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Can be baked in regular oven for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs. Stir in sour cream and vanilla. Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda. Blend together with egg mixture. Mix well. Put in large pan and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Serve with hot corn muffins.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Heat oil, saute onion.
Add carrots and peas, stir fry 2 minutes.
Add chicken.
Add egg and scramble.
Stir in rice and cooked until heated.
Add soy sauce, cook and stir until headed through.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: pineapple dish
directions: Put butter in bowl and melt.
Put pineapple in, followed by sugar.
Stir.
Next, put bread pieces in and stir again.
Heat in microwave for about 5 minutes.
Take out, stir and serve hot.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place half batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Put rest of batter in and top with remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° until a wooden pick inserted comes out clean, approximately 30 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over pickles and onion and let stand for 3 hours. Stir once in awhile.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar and add celery seed.
Drain pickles and onion.
Pour vinegar mixture over pickles. Put in refrigerator over night.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, margarine, vanilla and eggs,
mixing
well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over top of
sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter or margarine, powdered sugar, flour and salt as for pie crust.
Pat into a 10 x 14-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: In small bowl combine cream cheese, sour cream, avocado dip, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Blend well.
Spread mixture on large serving plate.
Top with remaining ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add to all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with Fritos chips and cheese sprinkled on top of chili.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook in large 9 x 12-inch buttered casserole dish at 350°
for 15 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered (30 minutes in all).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute
onions and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender.
Add
tomato paste, water with flour blended in, sugar and Worcestershire.
Stir until smooth and slightly thickened. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: best refrigerator rolls
directions: In large bowl, pour hot water over shortening, sugar and salt. Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add flour; blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 4 hours before making into rolls.
Make rolls and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 425°.

title: fish batter for perch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Have grease hot and deep-fry perch (or any fish) until golden brown.

title: bucket of muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; mix all liquid ingredients.
Put liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Refrigerate in tight container.
Keeps a month.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake as needed.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and sugar in mixing bowl and let stand 10 minutes.
Blend oil, vanilla and egg with the apples.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in raisins. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 9 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Mix thoroughly and press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Add unbeaten egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients gradually mixing thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll in white sugar; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and add Hershey Kiss on top.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice and soups in a deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle dry soup over top; then seal with foil. Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: sippin' cider salad(in honor of "washpa eagle")
directions: Bring juice or cider to a boil.
Pour over jello to dissolve. Drain cherries, cut in halves, and save juice.
Measure cherry juice and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into gelatin.
Set aside 2 cups of gelatin.
Keep at room temperature.
Chill remaining gelatin until partly set.
Fold in cherries, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold or 8 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: thai beef with noodles(30 minutes)
directions: Combine sherry, soy sauce, ginger, garlic, sesame oil and pepper pods.
Place beef steak in plastic bag; add marinade. Close bag securely and marinate 15 minutes. Pour off marinade; reserve.
Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add steak and cook 12 to 15 minutes for rare (140°) to medium (160°), turning once.
Remove steak, keep warm.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons cornstarch in reserved marinade and 1/4 cup water; add to skillet. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in noodles.
Carve steak into thin slices and serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party mix
directions: In
a
saucepan,
melt margarine, butter, sugar, garlic powder,
ajinomoto	and
Worcestershire
sauce.
In a separate large
pan, add cereal and nuts.
Pour melted ingredients over and mix.
Bake at 250° for about 1 1/2 hours, mixing every 15 minutes, until well coated.
Cool.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Roll in flour and brown in hot grease. When brown, pour off most of the grease.
Slice onion and add to grease, browning well.
Add chopped tomatoes (pour this over the chops and onions).
Cover with tight lid, turn heat down and allow to cook slowly until well done.
Serve with grits.

title: sour cream cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Gradually add eggs (one at a time). Add flour and cornstarch; mix well.
Add butter.
Fold in vanilla and sour cream.

title: barb's spaghetti sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes or put through juicer.
Then add all ingredients together and cook until it thickens.
(Remember, it's thicker when cold.)
Then put in hot jars and seal.

title: spinach balls
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: cathie's brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix cake mix, 3/4 cup melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup nuts.
Put 2/3 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Pour chocolate chips and caramel mixture over cake.
Top with remaining batter and bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Cut up Granny Smith and Delicious apples into slices.
Put in water with Fruit-Fresh. Put dip in dish. Surround with drained apples.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and sweet pepper very fine and set aside. Mix in a
saucepan
the vinegar, sugar, vegetable oil, salt, celery seed and
mustard
seed.
Bring
to a boil.
When cool, pour over
vegetables.
Cover
and
refrigerate
for
24 hours. Keeps well!

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and well beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add alternately with sour milk and bananas.
Add flavoring (vanilla) and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Test with tester.
Makes 2 layer 9-inch cake.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding and Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple. Add nuts and marshmallows.
Can be molded.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Dice potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain potatoes well. Using ricer, rice potatoes into a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and whip until fluffy.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with mini marshmallows.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until marshmallows are golden.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger.
Place the remaining ingredients into a crock-pot.
When the cheese is melted, spoon the drained meat into the mixture and stir together.
Let it simmer 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix soup and water.
Beat in eggs with a fork.
Let stand a while.
Shape meat into about 40 meatballs.
Brown in skillet or oven.

title: cheese-pineapple salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Dissolve sugar in pineapple syrup over low heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: st. patrick's treat
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix with pineapple and Cool Whip.
Add pudding mix.
Refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients, then mix remaining.
Put into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: ham-orange mini muffins
directions: For the
filling,
in
a small mixing bowl, combine the softened cream
cheese,
milk, finely shredded orange peel and the dry mustard;
mix well. Fold in the sour cream dip and the finely diced ham.

title: erin's sour cream cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° until done.
Check every half hour.
Done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain if necessary.
Let meat cool while putting the rest of salad together.
Put chili over top if you wish.

title: spanish omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt butter and cocoa. Cream eggs, sugar, salt and flour. Combine butter and egg mixture and mix well. Add nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or more. Remove from oven and cover with miniature marshmallows for about 10 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, light corn syrup, and water in large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, without stirring until temperature reaches 310 degrees.
Remove from heat; add food coloring and oil.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool, then break into pieces,
and roll in powdered sugar to coat.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray jelly roll pan with Pam.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar together.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto batter.
Cut through batter with knife or metal spatula several times for marbeled effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: penne arrabbiatta(italian for angry pasta)
directions: Cook penne according to directions. Cover bottom of baking dish with pasta sauce. Sprinkle Italian seasoning over top of sauce. Sprinkle crushed red pepper over sauce. Add cooked penne. Pour the olive oil over cooked pasta. Toss mixture.

title: dad's own "bubble and squeak"
directions: Pound flour into meat on both sides.
Cut in serving portions and brown in cooking oil.
Cook at low heat in heavy iron skillet with water while you are chopping onion and celery.
Then add salt, pepper, garlic or garlic salt.
Next add monosodium glutamate, if desired, onion, celery and soup.
Cook gently and slowly over low heat, covered, 45 minutes or until tender.
Turn once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix water and Jell-O and chill until hardly set.
Then mix the other things separate (cream cheese and sugar together).
When all are mixed, add milk last.
Combine and mix.
Pour into crust. Make graham cracker crust using 1 pack graham crackers and melted oleo and a little bit of sugar (1/4 cup oleo).

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add flour with baking powder and salt, mixed one spoonful at a time, with milk.
Add teaspoon of vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pineapple with juice and blend well.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Best if refrigerated for a few hours or overnight.

title: scalloped sausage and potatoes
directions: In skillet, break sausage into small pieces; brown lightly and drain well.
Place half of the potatoes in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of the flour and half of the salt on the potatoes.
Top with half of the sausage and half of the cheese. Repeat for second layer.
Pour milk over all.
(It helps to heat the milk.)
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes to brown.

title: texas style beans
directions: Cook beef and onions in small amount of fat.
Cook slowly until done.
Drain fat.
Add everything else.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Can cook in crock-pot.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add hot water to onion soup mix; stir.
Add rice, margarine, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Place broccoli in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Pour rice mixture over broccoli.
Cover with a tight fitting lid.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: sicilian whitefish
directions: Put the olive oil in bottom of pan (approximately 9 x 13-inch).
Mix the oil and fish together.
Cover fish with onion slices.
Cover with a mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° (covered) for 30 minutes more.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in cupcake papers in muffin pans and freeze.
After salads are frozen, they may be removed from muffin pans and stored in plastic bags in freezer.
Makes 12 salads which are nice to keep on hand for company.
Remove 30 minutes before serving and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: dill dip (for vegetables)
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh tomato tart
directions: Fit pie crust into a 10-inch tart pan, according to package directions.
Trim any excess pastry along edges.
Generously prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese evenly into pastry shell and top with basil to cover.
Arrange tomato slices on top; brush with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place tart on a baking sheet on lower rack of oven.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven;
sprinkle with remaining basil.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw the broccoli, then mix in all other ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beer batter halibut
directions: Dip fish in batter and then pan or deep fry.

title: bacon, egg and cheese strata
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and break into small pieces.
Cube bread and alternate layers of bread, cheese and bacon in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch bacon dish.

title: ida baird's buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and slowly add sugar.
Add flour, milk, oleo and flavoring.
Pour into crust.
Heat oven to 450°.
Lower to 350° when pie is placed in oven.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and rub with garlic.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Melt oil and butter in skillet.
Brown chicken.
Remove chicken and place in casserole.
Add mushrooms, water, wine and parsley.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender. Baste, adding more water if needed.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is dissolved and mixture cooled to lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, and the egg.
Mix well. Stir in flour to make soft dough.
Rub surface with Crisco, cover tightly and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will keep about 1 week.
When ready to use dough, punch down and roll out on floured board about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Brush with butter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Allow to rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until the redness is gone.
Take off stove. In casserole, place a layer of sliced potatoes, layer of onions, layer of ground meat, salt and pepper.
Continue layers until potatoes, onions and meat are used up.
Take tomato soup and dilute with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over the top of mixture.
Place bacon on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: cranberry surprise pie
directions: Spread cranberries, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts into greased 12-inch pie plate.
Beat thoroughly eggs; add 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Add in flour and shortening; mix well.
Pour over berries and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: tuna enchiladas
directions: Drain tuna and combine with cheese.
Cook onion and garlic in oil.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Place tuna mixture in tortillas and roll.
Place over sauce.
Pour over remaining sauce and top with cheese.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Soak beans in water overnight or cover beans with water.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cover and stand for 1 hour.
Without draining beans, add ham hocks, bay leaves and additional water if needed to cover the beans.
Simmer for 1 hour or until beans are just tender.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes (if large, cut into halves), salt, thyme, black pepper and cloves, if used.
Mix carefully until blended.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes until meat is tender.
Remove meat from ham hocks; discard fat and bones.
Return meat to pot.
Heat through and serve.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
In a cup, put egg, vanilla and milk.
Beat with fork.
Put margarine in powder mixture, add liquid ingredients.
Beat with electric beater until glossy or shiny.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: First, mix crumbs together (flour, sugar and shortening) until size of a pea.
Take out about 1 cup and set aside.
Mix liquids (hot water, molasses and baking soda), stir together and add your crumbs and fill pie shells 3/4 full.
Sprinkle your crumbs on top. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not open oven until done.

title: pear and lime jello salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Put pears and cream cheese in blender; liquefy.
Bring juice to a boil.
Dissolve Jell-O and cool.
Pour into cream cheese mixture, then fold into Cool Whip.

title: fruit rings
directions: Crumble mincemeat into 1/2 cup water and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour in bowl to cool.
Add fruit, part of flour, nuts, milk, beaten egg and then remaining flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Fill tiny muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased 9-inch pie plate or casserole dish at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden.
Serve warm with fruit or milk.
You can make it up the night before and bake in morning. Serves about 6 to 8.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in double boiler.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend well. Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except the oil, in blender.
Add oil slowly.
Beat several minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in a double boiler.
Add milk and stir.
Add pecans to mixture.
Drop a teaspoonful of the caramel on wax paper and let cool.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin in a double boiler.
Drop caramel mixture in chocolate mixture.
Put on wax paper.

title: fruit cheese pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese in mixer.
Blend in Cool Whip until smooth and well blended.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust (large size).
Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with 1 can fruit filling before serving.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together. Let chill in refrigerator for 1 hour. Serve with bread, crackers or Chinese noodles. Makes 8 servings.

title: lloyd's bread or rolls
directions: Form and
let
rise in pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. For rolls, follow the same instructions as before, but form into rolls and let rise until double in size.

title: red cabbage
directions: Finely chop or shred 1 head of cabbage and put it into a pot holding water to a depth of about 2-inches.
Core 1 onion and pack it with cloves.
Place it in the center of the cabbage.
Add 1 sweet apple, diced fine.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Add wine vinegar, sugar and oil.
Simmer.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 pound butter.
Boil cubed potatoes and drain.
Combine all ingredients and heat, but don't boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix together crushed pretzels, margarine and sugar. Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan. Saute onion and green pepper in drippings. Add all ingredients together. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and milk.
Melt margarine and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch uncooked pie crust and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Be sure to add pecans to batter before placing in oven.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix and keep in covered container.

title: baked pork chops with potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put in baking pan and on top put onions, potatoes and chicken stock.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with crushed Rice Krispies in 1/4 cup margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna-melon dinner salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Blend 1/2 cup reduced fat mayonnaise or salad dressing and 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Add to tuna mixture and toss lightly.
Serves 8.

title: easy quick soup
directions: *May add onion, garlic, cauliflower, broccoli and barley.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Prepare cake as it says on the box.
After cake is done, punch holes all over the cake with a fork.
Mix strawberry jello and strawberry pop together.
Bring to a boil, then pour it all over the cake.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Press half of crumb mix into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread with raspberry preserves. Sprinkle remaining mixture over preserves.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars or squares.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: Heat medium size nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add turkey.
Cook, breaking up meat with spoon until no longer pink. Place in colander to drain.
Wipe skillet clean with paper towel. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper, oregano, cumin and chili powder.
Cook uncovered for 6 minutes or until softened, stir occasionally.
Add turkey, tomato sauce, barbecue sauce and olives.
Bring to simmer; cook 5 minutes. Serve on rolls or over rice.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine brown sugar and syrup in a saucepan.
Heat until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over slightly crushed corn flakes.
Mix; drop onto buttered pan or waxed paper.

title: potato and green bean salad
directions: Cook potatoes according to package directions.
Drain in colander under cool running water, 30 - seconds.
Set aside.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Blend oil, eggs, water and pudding together, then add cake mix.
Oil a Bundt pan.
Combine pineapple and brown sugar.
Pour into pan.
Top with cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes in pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Cook dough on cookie sheet according to package; cool.
Spread mixture on dough.
Add veggies.
Cut in squares.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon and sausage. Scramble eggs. Stir bacon, sausage and eggs together in 9x13 inch baking dish. Spread cheese over mixture. Prepare 2 cups Bisquick according to label on box. Spread over cheese mixture. Cut butter into small pieces and place on top of Bisquick mixture. Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until top is golden. Gravy is excellent on top of this heart stopping breakfast treat.

title: granola
directions: Mix together all but last two ingredients.
Blend honey and oil with a beater until thoroughly blended.
Mix with dry ingredients, rubbing with fingers until dry ingredients are totally coated.
Spread on two large cookie pans.
Bake at 275° to 300° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter until softened. Lightly beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add beef, stuffing mix, cheese, parsley, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine gently, but thoroughly.
Form into loaf shape about 8 x 4-inches.
(Can make individual loaves.)
Place on a cookie sheet covered with foil. Beat remaining egg with water.
Separate rolls and lay over top and sides of loaf, sealing edges with egg water glaze.
Brush with remaining glaze.
Bake about 1 hour.
Serve with easy gravy (1 package gravy mix, 1/2 cup port wine and 1/2 cup water; mix according to directions on gravy mix).

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Drain shrimp; rinse in cold water.
Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add tomato paste and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add parsley and oregano.
Place pizza crusts on well greased baking pans.
Cover each crust with 1/3 of the sauce, 1/3 shrimp and 1/3 cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: violet's salmon patties
directions: Form into patties.
Brown in Mazola smeared frying pan.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat in sugar and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Blend in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate to set 3 to 4 hours.
Top with any kind of fruit.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cover peppers with water and let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Add onions with sugar, salt and vinegar; heat mixture to boiling point, 45 minutes and simmer 45 minutes.

title: martha hendrix's cheese krispies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Mix in flour gradually, adding pepper and salt.
Add Rice Krispies and work in completely.
Roll into small balls, then flatten with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes a lot!

title: pecan brittle
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Cook until it starts to yellow.
Add soda.
Spread on foil.
Let cool, then break up.

title: scalloped corn and hamburger with potatoes
directions: In frypan, brown hamburger and onion. Drain off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Spray casserole dish with cooking spray.
Place sliced potatoes in bottom of dish. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water. Shake 1/2 teaspoon salt over potatoes.
Put hamburger and onion mixture over potatoes. Spread creamed corn over.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Mix well.
Cook on low 4 hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Then add carrots and dry ingredients and mix.
Place into hot loaf pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, brown sugar, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with chopped onion.
Place in casserole. Pour soup over meat.
Place cheese slices over soup.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: elizabeth mingo's corn light bread
directions: Sift together 4 dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and vegetable oil.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes in loaf pan.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into hot oil (2 black skillets or 2 pans). If making one pan (half recipe), still use 1 egg. Bake at 450° until brown. Serves 12. Can freeze.

title: quick-n-easy popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in a heavy 2-quart size pan. Slowly add marshmallows; stir constantly until marshmallows are thoroughly melted.
(Food coloring may be added at this point for tinted popcorn.)
Pour over popped corn, coating entire batch of popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: russian salad
directions: Heat jello, water, marshmallows and cream cheese over low heat until marshmallows are dissolved and cream cheese is melted.
Add mayonnaise, milk, crushed pineapple with juice, bananas and pecans.
Mix all together with jello-cream cheese mixture.
Pour in mold or casserole dish; chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce or plain.

title: mexican polenta pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4 inches. Mix cornmeal, water and salt in medium 2 qt. saucepan. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat to medium. Cook about 6 minutes, stirring frequently, until mixture is very thick. Remove from heat quickly; let stand 5 minutes, stir in egg. Spread cornmeal mixture in pie plate. Bake uncovered 15 minutes. Spread beans over cornmeal mixture; sprinkle with cheese and corn chips. Bake uncovered 20 minutes or until center is set. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. This has 22 grams carbohydrates, and with a salad, makes a great meal.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
How easy is that!

title: apple-walnut ring
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
In small bowl, stir together the sifted flour, baking soda, mace and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to butter and sugar. Stir in vanilla, sliced apples and finally the chopped nuts. Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 90 minutes (1 1/2 hours).
Let cake cool in pan 10 minutes.
Shake out onto rack and cool.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Shred cheeses and set aside.
Mix undiluted soups, sour cream, cream cheese, taco seasoning mix, pimientos, mushrooms, black olives and peppers.
Bring to a low boil.
Remove from heat and add chicken.
Butter sides and bottom of 4 to 6-quart Dutch oven. Beginning with the flour tortillas, start to alternate tortillas, mixture and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes before serving, covered.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Peel, pit and slice fruit into crust.
Mix cream; beat until stiff or use Cool Whip.
Prepare pudding, using only 1 cup milk. Fold whipping cream (or Cool Whip) and lemon extract into pudding. Carefully spoon over peaches.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes before serving.
(Do not fold cream mixture into peaches, as the fruit tends to weep.)

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce and place in a large bowl.
Add celery, then bell pepper, peas and onions.

title: little league casserole
directions: Slice onion and separate into rings.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with onion rings.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Place on top of onion rings.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread uncooked ground beef over the potatoes.
Next spread the pork and beans over the meat.
Spread undiluted tomato soup evenly over the pork and beans.
Cut bacon strips in half and arrange on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Arrange triangles of cheese on top the last minutes of the baking time. Serves 4 to 6 people.
Leftovers are tasty heated in the microwave.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, butter, eggs and vinegar.
Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until firm in the center.

title: simple scalloped potatoes(cooking time 30 minutes)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine potatoes, flour, salt and onion.
Toss lightly.
Stir in milk and butter.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes, or until milk is just about to boil.
Stir mixture, then cook on Defrost 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let stand, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika or parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: First go through beans; take out rocks and bad looking beans and discard them.
Rinse beans under cool running water in a colander.
Put them in a 5-quart Dutch oven with 4 quarts of water. Bring to a boil; let boil for 2 minutes.
