Cover; turn off heat and let beans set in water for 1 hour.
Next, dump off old water from beans; don't pour out your beans.
Refill pan with fresh water. Return to a boil and then lower the heat to a gentle simmer. Simmer beans for 2 hours, until beans are tender.
You have to take one out and eat it to tell.
After first hour, add ham slices that you have chopped into half-inch squares (approximately).
Thirty minutes later, add soup mix and the salt and pepper to taste. Don't let the liquid get too low; if it does, beans will scorch. Just add more water and stir often.
You can add one handful of long grain rice or Minute rice during the last 30 minutes if you like the soup on your beans thick.
If you add rice, cook at least 20 more minutes.
Don't use a thin pan or your beans will scorch! Serve with cornbread.

title: nana's hot cocoa
directions: Put the cocoa and sugar into a cup.
Gradually stir in 2 teaspoons of the milk.
Stir to make a paste.
Pour the rest of the milk into a small saucepan.
Heat it over low heat just until a few tiny bubbles form around the edge of the saucepan.
Pour the milk into a cup and stir very well.
Serves 1.

title: french-style green beans
directions: Steam green beans whole until tender.
Melt butter in large pan.
Add chopped shallots, garlic and curly parsley.
Saute until tender, but not brown.
Add green beans and mix well.

title: meal in quiche
directions: You will need vegetable spray.

title: raw cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and stir well.
Cover and allow to stand at room temperature about 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until just blended.
Drop 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream the butter.
Add eggs and vanilla. Combine sugar and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts (and peanut butter chips, if you wish). Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown in a 350° oven.
Makes 8 to 10 servings because this is a very rich pie.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Slip out yolks.
Set whites aside, and mash yolks.
Add mayonnaise, pepper and dry mustard to egg yolks.
Mix well.
Heap yolk mixture lightly onto egg halves. Arrange filled eggs on serving plate and sprinkle with paprika. Serves 6.

title: spiced tea
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
To serve, add 3 teaspoons of the mix per glass of hot water.
Easy to store and easy to use.

title: aunt maud's orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and beat again.
Sift soda with flour and add alternately with sour milk.
Put whole orange (no seeds) through food chopper with a fine blade.
Add to batter with raisins.
Bake on a sheet pan at 450° for 10 minutes. Frost with boiled frosting.

title: diane's lasagna
directions: Boil noodles separately.
Mix hamburger meat with seasoning. Cook according to directions. Drain noodles.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat the first 3 ingredients in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar and spread on warm crust.
Slice fruit on top.
Cook remaining ingredients until thickened and drizzle over fruit.
Serve chilled.
Real good with whipped cream topping.

title: caramel pie
directions: Bake 2 pie shells.
Brown 3/4 cup white sugar until desired color.
Pour in 1/2 cup hot water and dissolve.
Mix 2 cups sugar and flour together.
Beat egg yolks and milk.
Mix with sugar, flour and browned sugar mixture, then add margarine and cook until thickened.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shells.

title: mock crab salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water until tender but firm; drain and add the remaining ingredients. Mix well. If desired, 2 hard boiled eggs may be added.

title: powdered sugar
directions: Place ingredients in blender jar. Cover and blend until Splenda Granular is a very fine powder.

title: squaw corn
directions: In a skillet, brown the luncheon meat and onion.
Add the corn and cook until bubbly.
Add the eggs and turn the heat down to low.
Stir occasionally until eggs are set.
Sprinkle in the chives and serve at once.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until thoroughly mixed.
Add buttermilk and yeast; work together until flour is moist.
Cover and put in refrigerator until ready to use. Roll 1/2-inch thick; let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
This recipe will make 6 dozen.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.
Take out what you need at a time.
Use a jigger for cutting biscuits out.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water together.
Let cool, but not set.
Add orange sherbet.
Add the orange slices and crushed pineapple.

title: mary stringer's dill pickles
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Prepare quart jars with alum, garlic, dill and cucumbers.
For a little extra spice, add 1/2 banana pepper to the jars.
Pack jars, pour brine in until 1/2 inch below rim of jar.
Seal and leave on surface, cover with a towel to avoid draft (do not process).

title: tarragon chicken(serves 10)
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish.
Pour buttermilk over chicken, cover tightly and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Pour off buttermilk and discard.
Dry chicken with paper towels.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cornstarch and nutmeg; cook until thick. Add one stick margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake about 20 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: "christmas jello mold"
directions: You will need one Bundt pan or jello mold.

title: ice tea punch
directions: Steep your tea bags in the 2 cups of hot water for 10 minutes, adding the sugar while hot.
Add extracts, lemon juice and cold water.
This is your punch base and may be refrigerated for a few days.
Add pineapple juice and ginger ale when it is time to serve.
Serves approximately 50 punch cups.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, bread, milk, egg, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt slightly.
Spread mix evenly in a 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain excess fat from meat loaf.
Prepare instant potatoes, spread over meat.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 4
to 5 servings.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 450° oven.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions.
Let cool. Mix softened cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise together.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Top with chopped vegetables of your choice.
Refrigerate.
Serve and enjoy!

title: old-fashioned strawberry soda
directions: In a blender container, combine first 5 ingredients. Cover and process until smooth. Pour into 2 tall glasses. Add ginger ale and serve immediately. Yield: 2 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add 1 cup flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Then add 1 cup flour over the fruit.
Mix well.
Then add batter to fruit and nuts.
Put in tube pan.
Shake well to make settle and then put in cold oven.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix lemon juice, oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken in shallow casserole or baking pan.
Pour over lemon and oil mix.
Cover and bake until tender (40 minutes), basting occasionally.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer to allow chicken to brown.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: play doh(not edible)
directions: Mix together ingredients except water and food coloring.
Add water to make a soft dough, then divide dough into equal parts. Add enough food coloring to make colors you desire.
When dough gets too hard to work with, add water again to soften.
Store in airtight containers.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Place one layer of ground beef in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish (sprayed with Pam).
Cover potatoes with ground beef, then place frozen vegetables on top. Mix soup with 1/2 can of water and pour over top of vegetables. Cover with foil and bake in 375° oven for approximately 2 hours.

title: elaine jordan's chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine canned ingredients and seasoning.
Mix well and stir in chicken, vegetables and cheese.
Mix with spaghetti and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fried chicken broccoli
directions: Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle ginger and pepper over chicken.
In large fry pan or wok, pour oil and heat to high temperature.
Add chicken and stir-fry 3 minutes or until brown. Push chicken aside and add broccoli and onion.
Stir-fry 3 minutes more.
Mix together 3/4 cup broth, salt and sugar; stir into fry pan.
Reduce heat to medium high; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch to remaining 2 tablespoons chicken broth; stir until smooth.
Stir into fry pan; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in Parmesan cheese; sprinkle with whole wheat croutons.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great side dish with ham or chicken.

title: cut glass jello salad
directions: Add 1 1/2 cups hot water to each box of lime, strawberry and black cherry Jell-O.
Put in separate pans and let jell. Add pineapple juice and sugar together in saucepan and let it come to boil. Remove from heat and add raspberry Jell-O.
Let set until slightly thick.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on box. Add raspberry mixture. Cut lime, strawberry and black cherry Jell-O into small squares and add to raspberry mixture.
Let set 24 hours.

title: minestrone soup with ground beef
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat, cook ground beef, onion, celery and cabbage, stirring until all pan juices evaporate and meat and vegetables are lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garbanzo beans and corn, all with their liquid, zucchini, macaroni, bouillon, basil leaves and 3 cups water over high heat. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer soup 8 to 10 minutes until macaroni and vegies are done.

title: caf cappuccino
directions: Process in blender on liquefy until blended. Store in airtight container.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine
cake mix,
egg and margarine.
Press into rectangular (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: transparent pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Put meringue on top and bake until brown. This is similar to Chess Pie.

title: weight watchers bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and tear into small pieces.
Beat together all other ingredients.
Pour over bread in small baking dish.
Let set 1 minute.
Sprinkle cinnamon and put diet margarine on top.
Scald milk in microwave for 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Great for breakfast.

title: microwave baked apple
directions: Core apples and slice the skin around the circumference 1/2-inch from top.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil; cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.

title: adean's baked chicken
directions: Wrap chicken in dried beef and bacon.
Secure with toothpick if desired.
Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, cream cheese and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 200° to 250° for 2 hours.

title: egg mcmuffin
directions: Microwave bacon (5 strips) approximately 4 1/2 minutes. Microwave egg 1 minute and 15 seconds in a cup covered with paper towel.
Place egg on toasted English muffin, top with cheese (Cheddar and Swiss).
Microwave for 45 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Amounts depend on how many there are to serve.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine tomatoes, margarine, lemon juice and salt in a saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix flour, cinnamon and sugar together and add to the tomato mixture.
Simmer for a few minutes longer, until thickened.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Tastes like apple pie.
This is an old one, been around for a long time.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and cool spaghetti.
Next, mix spaghetti with all other ingredients.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine, vanilla and egg to make a crust.
Beat cream cheese, 10x sugar, eggs and vanilla together until smooth.
Press crust in cookie sheet.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut in bars.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Break cake into medium pieces in a large container.
Mix powdered sugar and milk. Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Stir this into broken cake.
Mix glaze and thawed strawberries.
Use crystal bowl. Use cake mixture for first layer, then spread with strawberry mix. Repeat.
Chill overnight.

title: iced coffee
directions: In a bowl, dissolve coffee in water. Add sweetener. Stir in milk, chocolate syrup and vanilla extract; mix well. Serve over ice.

title: big wheel chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Mix together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Add pecans.
Drop by scant 1/4 cup onto baking sheet and slightly press down on centers. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add dry ingredients, sour cream, chips and nuts.
Blend and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool on racks.

title: peanut soup
directions: Cut beef, smoked turkey or chicken (you may use all 3 if you desire) into manageable sizes; boil.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Add tablespoon of oregano, ginger powder, dill seed powder, celery powder, a can of tomato paste or sauce and 2 to 3 tablespoons of peanut butter.
Boil all of these ingredients for about an hour or two.
Serve over rice, potatoes, grits or bread.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well to form crust.
Place cherry pie filling in pie pan and spread crust on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: aussie cheese fries
directions: Fry frozen fries in oil.
Drain excess grease.
Top with Mozzarella, American, Monterey Jack combination shredded cheese. Crumble fried bacon on top.
Microwave for 45 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: mrs. mac's christmas squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and divide into 3 parts.
Color 1 part green, 1 part red and leave 1 part white.
In a 9 x 9-inch or 10 x 10-inch pan layer the mixtures.
White layer first, followed by the red and then the green layer.
Let stand several days before cutting into squares.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: 1st:
Mix together flour, butter and nuts.
Press in baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of pan, then a layer of pie filling. Sprinkle box of dry cake mix next.
Pour melted butter over dry cake mix.
Add layer of nuts and coconut.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for about 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian hot dish
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good with hot dogs, also.

title: pickle roll-em-ups
directions: Spread one side of each ham slice with one tablespoon of cream cheese.
Place one pickle on edge of each ham slice.
Roll ham around pickle.
Press edge to seal.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apple.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
(If you use white grapes, add them at this time so they can absorb the color.)
Add grapes, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: chestnut falls chicken
directions: Cut raw chicken into bite-sized pieces; place in a buttered 9 1/2 x 11-inch dish.
Saute vegetables in margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Add seasonings.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven. Serve over wild rice.

title: chicken casserole(club member: brad smith)
directions: Debone chicken; mix with soups and sour cream. Top with crushed Ritz crackers mixed with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients (sugar, peanut butter, syrup) over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Press into well greased cookie sheet. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over mixture.

title: dave titus' shrimp remoulade
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and chill.
When ready to serve, arrange peeled shrimp on lettuce and pour sauce over the shrimp.

title: baked beef
directions: Combine all in large casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Mix gelatin with 1/2 cup cold water in a bowl; let stand about 5 minutes.
Add boiling water; mix well to dissolve.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, Tabasco, paprika and salt.
Stir salmon into mixture.
Whip cream until fairly stiff; fold into the salmon mixture.
Pour into a greased mold or bowl; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Turn out onto a plate.
Before serving, garnish with celery slices, olives and lemon wedges.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and dry fresh broccoli.
Just cut off the flower tops. Put in bowl and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Best if made the night before so flavors sets.
Refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, milk and yeast mixture.
Knead, roll out and let rise 5 minutes before baking.
Bake in oven at 475°.

title: carol's pie crust
directions: Measure flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into large mixing bowl.
Add Crisco and mix.
Beat 1 egg in a 1 cup or larger measuring cup; add vinegar and fill the measuring cup with cold water to 1 cup mark.
Stir, then mix egg and water into flour and Crisco mixture, stirring with a fork.
Mix well.
This is a moist and sticky dough and up to 2 additional cups of flour may be used in rolling dough.

title: canadian white christmas cake
directions: Mix fruits in large bowl.
Sift flour and baking powder over fruit.
Mix with hands to thoroughly cover fruit.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, oil of lemon, sugar, butter and coconut. Pour over flour and fruit. Bake 2 hours first hour at 275° and second hour bake at 300°. Makes 2 large loaves.

title: golden crumb broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients, except crackers.
Put broccoli in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over.
Top with crumbs/croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli stuffing casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Melt margarine.
Add cheese and soup.
Then add broccoli and onion to cheese mixture and stuffing. Mix well.

title: salsa
directions: Peel, chop and drain tomatoes.
Chop onion and pepper. Combine all ingredients; cook until thick as desired.
Put in hot jars.
Pressure cook at 5 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix the berries with sugar. Let stand overnight. Cook over low heat until the sugar dissolves. Then turn up the heat and cook fast for 20 minutes, skimming off foam while cooking. Add the lemon juice and mix. Turn the heat to low and let simmer for 20 minutes more. Store in sterilized jars, following general canning procedures.

title: cauliflower casserole(serving size: 8)
directions: Cook cauliflower until crisp-tender.
Drain and place in 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream, 1 tablespoon butter and pepper. Stir well.
Pour over cauliflower.

title: chocolate covered grasshoppers
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix dessert topping and liqueurs; beat on high speed until well blended and set aside.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave until just crisp tender along with onion and celery (you may use leftover vegetables).
Cook about 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix flour or cornstarch into vegetables mixture and add salt, pepper, parsley (and other favorite spice). Then pour into saucepan for on top of stove cooking.
Add milk and water at the same time and heat until just to a boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture thickens, add cubed cheese and stir until melted.
Simmer until vegetables are done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3, greased 8- inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles as usual.
Mix together chopped corned beef, onion and cheese.
Next, sprinkle in flour and mix thoroughly. Then stir in soup and milk.
In buttered casserole dish, place corned beef mixture and noodles in alternate layers.
Sprinkle top of casserole with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and add chili sauce, mustard, sugar and crushed pineapple.
Simmer.
Serves 6.

title: cavattini-cavattini
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Fry hamburger, onion and bell pepper until brown; drain.
Add sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni to noodles and heat.
Place in serving size bowls; sprinkle with cheese. Melt under broiler and serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of shell; bake 10 minutes at 425°. Cool.
Combine next seven ingredients; beat until blended.
Pour mixture into shell; bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Cool.
Combine next five ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Chill well.

title: peanut butter rice krispies bars
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to boil in a 2-quart pan.
Add butter; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir.
Pour over the Rice Krispies and marshmallows, which are ready in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Stir and pack down.
Cool and cut.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Place 1 biscuit in muffin cup.
Press dough up sides to edge of cups.
Spoon hot meat into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour Italian dressing over it.
Chill before serving.

title: fat-free chocolate cake(it's hard to believe that such a tasty cake is fat-free.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, cocoa, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, mix sugar and water.
Blend in egg whites and corn syrup.
Gradually stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer partially thawed hash browns over the butter.
Mix the cheese, soup and sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: hot dog corn supper
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1/2-inch pieces.
Brown hot dogs, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add the corn and stir.
Heat until corn is hot.
Serves four.

title: smoked sausage noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Melt butter in small saucepan over medium-high heat. Saute onion and celery until crisp-tender.
Combine noodles, onion, celery, corn, sour cream, salt and pepper in large bowl. Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Cut sausage into serving size pieces.
Arrange on top of noodles.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add finely chopped onion.
Mix in sugar, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Add cream; mix again. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Remove some seeds from chiles.
Lay 1/2 the chiles in bottom of well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with 1/2 the tortilla strips and 1/2 the cheese.
Top with tomato slices.
Repeat layers of chiles, tortillas and cheese.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Press in bottom of dish and cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip delight
directions: Dip each cookie in milk just to cover and back out.
Layer on bottom of large 1 1/2-inch deep, ungreased pan.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Repeat both layers until you get to the top of the pan.
Make sure you end up with Cool Whip on top.
Usually you will have two layers of each layer. If you prefer, you can make the top layer chocolate Cool Whip.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients in large bowl and put in ungreased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 375°, uncovered. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery; add cabbage.
Cook and stir until browned.
Stir in tomatoes, beans and water.
Season; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer.

title: cream sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and water until thick and lemon in color.
Add flavoring and sugar gradually and beat until sugar is dissolved. Mix and sift together flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into flour mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn upside-down on rack to cool.
Loosen from sides of pan when cool.
Delicious with strawberries and cream.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla and margarine.
Blend in rest.
Pour into shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Spread on Cool Whip.

title: spinach and blue cheese with steak(low carb)
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil; continue boiling 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.
(Must work quickly.)

title: rolls
directions: Mix ingredients as written.
Let rise until doubles.
Butter 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Roll dough out and cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Let rise again.
Cook in 350° oven until brown.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Place graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch container.
Mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip and pour over crackers, add another layer of crackers on top of filling.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on top of crackers.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Halve the grapes and cut up the rest of the fruit.
Beat eggs and put into a saucepan.
Add the rinds, juices and sugar.
Simmer slowly until the mixture thickens.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: eggplant salad with tomatoes and feta cheese
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place eggplant cut side up on broiler pan. Brush with 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Broil until golden, about 3 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Combine eggplant, tomatoes and basil in bowl.
Whisk 1 1/2 tablespoons oil, lemon juice and garlic in another bowl.
Add to eggplant.
Stir in Feta.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with olives.

title: garlic crabs
directions: Bring 8 quarts water to boil in a large pot.
Separate garlic into cloves, mash and add to boiling water with the salt, bay seasoning and bay leaf.
Add crabs.
Bring to a second boil. Remove crabs.
Remove claws from crabs.
Take off top shell. Clean, cut in half and put back in pot.
Let stand for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Take out all crabs and enjoy.
Great with beer or white wine.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Pour pineapple and juice over cake, then layer of pudding, layer of Cool Whip and layer of coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate with butter over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat after chocolate is completely melted.
In a mixing bowl, mix sugar and cornstarch; beat in eggs and add vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Mix pecans and coconut; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until top is puffed.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In a pan thoroughly stir together cornstarch, sugar and salt. Gradually stir in the boiling water, stirring constantly to keep it smooth.
Continue stirring and cook over moderate heat until boiling.
Boil gently 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon rind and juice.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve hot over apple cake. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: roast and relaxation
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, shake roast in flour.
Roll down top of a large Reynolds oven bag; put in sauce, water, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Squeeze bag gently to blend.
Place roast in bag. Peel and quarter carrots and onions; add celery, peppers and potatoes.
Turn bag gently to coat ingredients with sauce.
Close bag and make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake 1 3/4 to 2 1/4 hours at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: take it easy chicken
directions: Mix rice with soups and water in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 pkg. of onion soup mix over rice and soup.
Put chicken over this. Top with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover pan tightly with foil. Bake at 250 degrees for 2 1/2 hours.
(May need 1/4 c. more water.)

title: nana buckley's popovers
directions: Mix ingredients. Put in well greased cups.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes, then turn down to 300° for another 20 minutes. Watch em pop!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Spoon crab meat into mushrooms.
Brush with butter and sprinkle top with paprika. Broil in oven until crab meat is done.

title: char siu chicken
directions: Mix and marinate chicken overnight.
Cook over hibachi.

title: onion upside-down bread
directions: Peel and thickly slice onions.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter until golden and fairly soft.
Spread remaining 1 tablespoon butter in 9-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Arrange onion slices in baking dish.

title: charlotte de pommes(a.k.a.:  errol's apple charlotte, an unusual and delicious
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Remove cores and seeds and halve the quarters again; do not peel apples.
Place apples in a saucepan with the zest and juice of the lemons and cinnamon.
Cover pan; set over low heat until apples become tender, then mash apples and stir in jam.
Add sugar, vanilla, rum and 3 teaspoons of butter. Heat and stir often until sauce is very thick and stiff and holds its shape solidly on a spoon.

title: pear trifle
directions: Bake cake by package directions and allow to cool completely. Make jello.
Put pears in pan and pour 1/2 of the jello over pears.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and bone chicken. Save 1 cup broth from boiled chicken. Mix broth, tomatoes and soups in bowl.
In baking dish, layer crushed chip and chicken. Pour half sauce mixture. Sprinkle 1 cup cheese.
Repeat layers until all meat is used.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Let set for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut fruit cookies(diabetic)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until the consistency of peas.
Stir in coconut and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cool chicken.
Remove from bone.
Cut into bite-size pieces and set aside.
Thaw the broccoli so that it breaks up easily. Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk.
Spread frozen broccoli into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread chicken evenly over broccoli, then spread soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese evenly over soup.
Top with stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: braciole
directions: Trim all fat from steak. Cut into 8 equal pieces, then pound thin. Remove casing from Italian sausage. Break up in medium bowl. Add parsley, Parmesan cheese, garlic, Italian seasoning, 1 teaspoon salt and the lemon-pepper seasoning; mix thoroughly. Spread each steak with 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of sausage mixture. Roll up jelly roll fashion; fasten with toothpick. Brown rolls 3 to 4 at a time in hot oil in Dutch oven. Add onion and carrot to pot. Cook until vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in wine, tomatoes, tomato paste, remaining 1 teaspoon salt and bay leaf. Bring mixture to boil; lower heat. Add
beef rolls. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Remove from heat. Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: spanish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of mixture in oblong pan.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: rich egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side
up. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine together.
Add egg, oil and vanilla; begin adding oats, corn flakes, flour, soda and salt. Fold in nuts.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: diana's golden corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 regular size muffin cups or line with paper or foil baking cups.
Combine dry and wet ingredients, mixing only until just blended. Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into baking dish. Combine cornflakes, almonds and butter.
Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Beat salt and egg whites until mixture forms soft peaks.
Add sugar gradually until smooth and glossy.
Continue beating and add a little Karo syrup a little at a time, beating well after each addition until frosting peaks.
Fold in food coloring (optional) and vanilla.

title: caleb's quick and tasty cheese ball(appetizer)
directions: Chop scallions and dried beef into small pieces.
Mix in cream cheese.
With wet hands, form into ball and refrigerate 1 hour. May be rolled in finely chopped walnuts.

title: letcho
directions: Slice bacon into strips or squares and fry; drain off half of the fat.
Add chopped onion and peppers.
Fry until soft.
Add can of tomatoes and simmer for 15 minutes or so.
Salt to taste. This Hungarian dish can be eaten like soup or with rice, noodles or crusty bread.

title: peanut crunch cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and continue creaming. Add egg to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten each ball with fork tines.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: green vegetables in mustard sauce(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cook zucchini and shallots in butter in large heavy skillet until tender.
Stir in green beans, marjoram, thyme, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until hot through.
Combine sour cream, mustard and flour; stir into vegetables.
Heat and stir until hot and thickened.
Serve garnished with tomato wedges.

title: white punch
directions: Slice oranges and lemons.
Squeeze out juice and pour hot water over them. Add sugar.
Let stand until cool.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and pineapple juice.
Stir well.

title: greek biscotti
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs for 3 minutes. Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add to wet ingredients, beating until well mixed. Spread batter into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. This batter is stiff; you may need to lightly wet your hands with cold water and press into pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Invert onto rack and cool. Slice into thirds. Arrange cookies on cookie sheet and return to oven to bake until golden brown and crisp. Cool on rack.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks, applesauce.
Blend until smooth. Sift flour.
Add other dry ingredients.
Add together, then add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour in 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Slowly beat in milk.
Fold in peanut butter until creamy.
Add Cool Whip and fold until blended well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze with cover.
Serve with hot fudge sauce or plain.

title: italian steak
directions: Cook mushrooms, onion and green pepper in fat for 5 minutes. Blend in chili sauce, water, salt, pepper, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and olives.
Pour over steak.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: tamale pie
directions: To prepare mush, bring 4 cups water and 2 teaspoons salt to a boil in a large soup pot.
In a large bowl, add corn meal to 2 cups cold water; mix until smooth.
Add this mixture to the boiling water and cook on medium heat until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cover with lid; cool only enough to handle it.

title: roast chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Split chicken through back and leave the breast whole.
Put in baking pan with breast side up. Stuff with celery, onion and carrot.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan. Bake about 45 minutes, basting occasionally. Before chicken is done, add all seasoning and a can of cream of mushroom soup, diluted with water.
Baste again and continue to cook about 15 minutes or until done.

title: islander cheese dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and pineapple together with electric mixer. Stir in onion, salt and 1 1/2 cup nuts.
Cover with extra nuts and chill.
Scoop out pineapple, after cutting a pineapple lengthwise.
Use waxed paper to line inside of pineapple to prevent juice from making dip soggy.
Fill pineapple with chilled dip.

title: strawberry dessert crepes
directions: Heat an 8-inch nonstick skillet.
Combine eggs, milk and flour.
Let stand several minutes.
Meanwhile, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and half and half and whip until smooth and fluffy.
Also, over low heat, melt the strawberry preserves until liquidy.
Pour 2 tablespoons batter into skillet and immediately tilt pan until bottom is covered entirely.
When edges start to brown, turn crepe over to brown other side.
When all crepes are made, fill each with a tablespoon of cream cheese filling and roll up.
Dribble the melted strawberry preserves over the tops of the rolled crepes.
Garnish with fresh strawberries and serve.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill the chicken breasts over medium-hot coals for 15 to 18 minutes, turning once, or until tender and juices run clear. Remove from the grill and place in a single layer on a platter; sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside.
In a large bowl, toss pasta, red pepper, celery, onion and dill.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and butter. Blend at low speed until crumbly.
Stir in the nuts.
Press about 2 3/4 cups into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
To the remaining mixture add cinnamon, baking soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Stir in apples. Spoon over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream if desired.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: low-fat chili
directions: In a large pot, brown turkey. Drain any excess fat. Add onion, pepper and garlic. Stir until onion changes color.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
(One cup with 5 crackers equals 8 grams total fat.)

title: pecan chewies
directions: Cream oleo & sugar; beat eggs in one at a time.
Add flour and mix well, then add pecans.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes until done.

title: upside down peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.Lightly wipe the bottom of an 8-inch square cake pan with vegetable oil. Sprinkle the bottom of the pan evenly with the brown sugar. Arrange the peaches in the pan in a tight pinwheel pattern. Sprinkle with nutmeg or ginger. Set aside. In a mixing bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add the softened butter, buttermilk and vanilla extract; beat with an electric mixer until smooth. Pour the batter over the peaches, and bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour, until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: creamy cole slaw(40 calories per serving)
directions: Mix buttermilk, chives, sour cream, lemon juice, caraway seed, salt and pepper in a large glass or plastic bowl.
Add cabbage, carrot and onion.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Make crust following directions on package or use an 8-inch packaged crumb crust.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Blend in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Blend in whipping cream.
Pour into crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes (center will be soft but will set upon cooling).
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill several hours.
Garnish with pie filling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix with corn, 3 tablespoons of butter, eggs, Italian seasoned bread crumbs and chopped green pepper in 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Tear two slices of bread into small pieces and mix with 3 tablespoons of melted butter.
Place on top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: my western beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight or bring to boil for one minute. Turn off and soak 2 to 3 hours.
Cook until soft.
Fry bacon and ground beef.
Add vegetables and saute until soft.
Add to beans. Add remaining ingredients and let cook for several hours in slow cooker.
Adjust seasonings, if necessary.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Chop dates.
Set aside.
Blend pudding mix and biscuit mix. Cut in oleo.
Mix in egg, lemon juice and dates.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a tablespoon dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes. Cool.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Beat all together.
Bake in greased large iron skillet or any other appropriate baking pan at 350° to 400° for 40 to 45 minutes. Don't have the skillet hot like for regular corn bread, just warm enough to grease.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine and mix with everything but stuffing mix and place in casserole dish.
Put stuffing mix on top and slice pats of margarine over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reese bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, butter and graham cracker crumbs; spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 1 minute to set.
Spread melted chips over peanut butter mixture.
Chill and cut into squares.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spray casserole dish with Baker's Joy. Bake at 375° until it begins to brown.

title: small meat balls
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients into bite size meat balls.

title: salsa plus
directions: Chop all of the vegetables in bite-sized pieces in a 3-quart bowl. Add prepared salsa; mix and serve with corn chips of your choice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls together onto a pan; bake at 375°.
Let cool completely.
Blend well the cream cheese and mayonnaise; spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped raw vegetables of your choice.

title: oven bean soup
directions: Put all together and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: lemonade syrup
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add juice; strain.
Use 3 or 4 tablespoons syrup per glass.

title: rosie's hot tamales
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except corn flour, then roll out tamales to the size you prefer (three-inch tamales is my choice). Coat tamales by rolling in corn flour.
It should make 20 dozen. Put tamales in a large pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add to broccoli the sauteed onion, Cheez Whiz, undiluted soup and rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute margarine and mushrooms.
Add cooked broccoli, soup and cheese (melted).
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips.

title: peanut loaf(vegetarian)
directions: Saute pepper and onion until light brown.
Add to cooked rice. Add rest of ingredients and mix lightly.
Put in loaf pan or casserole and bake about 1 hour at 375°.

title: quick chili
directions: Saute
onions and green pepper in fat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add all other ingredients and simmer on low for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: I use 1 cup of nuts.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, gradually stir soup into cream cheese. Add milk, mustard and pepper.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Add macaroni, vegetables and Parmesan cheese. Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar; add butter, beaten eggs and coconut, then add milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Beat in thoroughly eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve slightly warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: salt cookies(not to be eaten)
directions: Blend salt and flour.
Add water a little at a time.
Knead dough 7 to 10 minutes until firm.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
use cookie cutters for shape.
Cut hole for hanging with a nailhead. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 325°.
When cool, paint, varnish or glitter.
Let dry.
String or use colored ribbon.
hang on your Christmas tree.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls the size of small walnuts.
Place into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: beef patties
directions: Put bread and water in a bowl. Add rest of the ingredients. Mix well and shape into four 1/2-inch thick patties.
Cook in greased frying pan over medium heat, turning once on both sides.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown onion and ground meat in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce. Simmer.
Boil large package of wide egg noodles and add sour cream and cream cheese.
Layer 1/2 noodles mixture, 1/2 sauce, 8 ounces or more of grated Cheddar cheese, 1/2 noodle mixture, 1/2 sauce and 8 ounces or more grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cut up broccoli in the bottom of rectangular, glass baking dish.
Put cut up chicken breasts on top.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle bread crumbs over the cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; blend with first mixture.
Add apples and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan while still hot.

title: momma mary's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Mix egg, milk and Pet milk well. Pour in flour and sugar mixture.
Stir vanilla and butter well and add to mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thickens.
Cool.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cut up cucumbers in pan and add 1 tablespoon of salt.
Drain. Add vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Let sit one hour.
Place in Ziploc bags.
Keep at least 24 hours in freezer before eating.
Good!

title: cheesecake dip
directions: *Any of these seasonings may be added.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each cookie with fork that is dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: crock-pot crab dip
directions: Combine the cream cheese and whipping into crock-pot. Cover and heat on high until the cheese is melted, about 45 minutes. Add the Parmesan cheese, crabmeat, onion soup mix, Worcestershire sauce and minced garlic and blend thoroughly. Cover; cook on high for 30 minutes. Shortly before serving, add the lemon juice and mix thoroughly. Salt to taste. Sprinkle the dip with fresh minced chives as the garnish. Serve with saltines, variety crackers or toast. This is a great appetizer around the holidays!

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 3/4-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Combine sauce, sugar and seasonings in a 1 1/2-quart casserole or serving dish. Cover.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until hot.
Stir in hot dogs; cover.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once. When hot, serve with cocktail picks.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: hash brown pie(diabetic and heart healthy)
directions: Press thawed hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Press into bottom and up sides of ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Combine ham, cheese and green pepper; spoon over crust. Mix eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour over hash browns.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with salsa.
Serves 6.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cola salad
directions: Pour off fruit juices; heat juices and enough water to make 2 cups to dissolve gelatin.
When mixture cools, add cola drink. After gelatin mixture has thickened slightly, add fruit and nuts to cream cheese.
Chill until mixture is firm before serving.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
In large pot, add beef, beans (include juice), tomatoes and chili powder to taste. Cook until beans are tender.

title: sunday roast
directions: Coat roast with Kitchen Bouquet and seal in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat before you leave for church to 250°; when you get home you will have a juicy, done roast ready to eat.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut and milk.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.
Set oven at 350° and grease cookie sheet.
Drop dough by teaspoon one-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes until brown.
Remove at once and cool.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender with salt and pepper to taste.
Bone chicken and put back in broth.

title: elaine bram's oatmeal bars
directions: Melt first
ingredients in a double boiler.
Mix all other ingredients together into a crumb mixture.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumb mixture
on
bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pat down.
Pour melted
mixture
over
top;
add
remaining crumb mixture.
Pat down.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: diabetic applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add and beat until light the egg.
Add vanilla and applesauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Blend well and drop by teaspoon onto lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: cornish game hens with stuffing
directions: Season game hens inside and out with salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, cook almonds, rice and onion in butter for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water, bouillon cube, lemon juice and salt.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring to dissolve cube.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer slowly about 20 to 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Stir in drained mushrooms.
Lightly stuff hens with rice mixture.
Place, breast up, on rack in shallow baking pan.
Brush with melted butter. Roast, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and roast 1 hour longer, basting with butter last 15 minutes.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Cut up artichoke hearts in quarters.
Mix with olive oil and bread crumbs to desired consistency.
Add cheese and oregano to taste.
Add water, about 1/4 cup so that it doesn't dry out.
Cook in microwave about 10 minutes on Medium.
If not hot enough, cook last minute or two on High.
Do not burn or dry out by overcooking.

title: autumn soup
directions: In a large pot, cook ground beef; drain fat.
Cook onions with meat until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Serves 6.

title: beef cup snacks(makes 10 snacks)
directions: Brown beef in frying pan; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, onion and both seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
Separate biscuits.
Place each one in bottom and up the sides of a greased (use Pam) muffin pan.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuit cup.
Sprinkle each with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fried chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken into desired pieces and season thoroughly with dry seasonings.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Combine water, eggs and Tabasco sauce in a large bowl.
Mix well until eggs are beaten. Place chicken in water mixture.
Let set for 30 minutes.
To obtain full flavor, let mixture set in refrigerator overnight. Drain water from chicken and dredge in flour again.
Place chicken in 375° oil until golden brown.

title: aunt marie's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pans.
Mix the first 9 ingredients; add flour, then mix in zucchini, nuts and raisins. Mix well.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: On wax paper, combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until browned on both sides.
Put chicken to side.
Stir in soup and water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with fresh thyme, if desired.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: caramelized potatoes and carrots
directions: Peel potatoes, trim carrots and place in large saucepan.
Cover with cold water, stir in salt.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until tender; drain.
In 10-inch heavy skillet, heat sugar over medium heat until sugar melts and becomes golden brown, stirring frequently with wooden spoon.
Stir in butter until almost melted.
Stir in cooked vegetables until evenly glazed (3 to 4 minutes).

title: piraeus greek meat pie
directions: Saute onion in oil in large skillet over medium heat until soft.
Add ground chuck, breaking up meat as it browns.
Stir in rice, chicken broth, cumin, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Feta and Ricotta cheeses, eggs, pecans and parsley.
Taste; add additional salt and pepper, if needed.

title: french fry pie
directions: In a electric skillet, fry 10 slices bacon.
Remove and drain about
4 tablespoons grease.
Place frozen French fries in pan and brown.
Sprinkle
with
salt
and
pepper to taste. Cover pan and cook over
low
heat until browned.
Mix 1 dozen eggs and pour over
browned
fries.
Reduce
heat
and
cover. Cook 3 minutes and add
bacon
and cheese and continue cooking for 5 to 10 minutes, until eggs are set.
Cut into squares and serve with cinnamon rolls and fruit.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind apricots.
Add coconut and milk.
Roll in small balls and roll in 10x sugar.
Keep uncovered a few hours to dry slightly.

title: pork chop pie
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and place in bottom of pan.
Fry pork chops, then drain excess grease, then place on top of potatoes. Pour mushroom soup from can onto pork chops and spread.
Place in oven; cook until potatoes are done.

title: little date nut loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 5 miniature loaf pans (4 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches).
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until blended.
Divide batter among prepared pans.
Decorate with cherries.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tex mex party dip
directions: Evenly spread refried beans on a 15-inch round platter.
In a mixing bowl, mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning until thoroughly mixed.
Spread evenly over beans.
Mix together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread this evenly over sour cream mixture.
Layer the next ingredients in this order: chopped tomatoes, green onions, olives and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Combine veggies.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic.
Pour over salad; toss.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top should be golden brown.

title: sunday morning breakfast casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish with hash browns. Brown onion and sausage; drain.
Spread over potatoes.
Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; season to taste.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 50 minutes.

title: tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes and combine with onion.
Combine rest of ingredients and toss into tomatoes and onion.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and shortening, in 2-quart saucepan, over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes; let cool.
Cut into about 2-inch squares.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Crush pretzels and add to melted chocolate.
Add peanuts and mix until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store in cookie tin or Ziploc bag.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen pieces.

title: root beer float
directions: In a glass, fill it 1/3 full with root beer.
Stir several spoonfuls of ice cream into root beer.
Pour glass 3/4 full with rootbeer.
Top with ice cream.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with whisk. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: "fireless cake"
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put waxed paper in deep large pan. Put layer of mixture.
Put a layer of cookies until all done. Press down.
Let sit in cool place (do not refrigerate) for 4 days.

title: apple torte
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures.
Bake in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Brush melted butter on top.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Sift half of dry ingredients into sugar mixture; blend.
Sift in remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well, then mix in pecans.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese and powdered sugar.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown or well done.

title: peach "no egg" ice cream
directions: Dissolve the gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add boiling water to completely dissolve the gelatine.
Place all ingredients (except peaches), including gelatine mixture, in blender; thoroughly blend.

title: my own crab soup
directions: Cut up bacon slices and simmer with onion in a large Dutch oven.
When bacon is brown and onions golden, add boiling water and tomatoes, cut up.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour or more.
If necessary, skim top.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss together; chill and serve.

title: southwest chili
directions: Pour oil in a large pot. Add diced chicken, garlic powder and onion powder. Saute chicken until it is no longer pink and juices run clear. Add beans (do not drain), salsa, cumin and cheeses. Stir. Add 1 cup of water. Cook 2 hours on medium/low heat.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion in butter, add potato, cut up broccoli, broth, a pinch of soda and boil 30 minutes.
Put in a blender a little at a time.
A very good soup; the potato is what thickens it.
Be sure to cover top of blender as it may spurt out.

title: hot turkey casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients together, except chips.
Pour into large baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed chips over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Good for leftover Thanksgiving or Christmas turkey!

title: haystacks
directions: In double boiler, mix all ingredients. When butterscotch is melted, dip out by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Split party rolls open.
Spread top and bottom with blended mixture.
Add ham to rolls and top with Swiss cheese.
Place rolls together.
Place rolls on aluminum foil and wrap tightly.
Heat in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Can be frozen and then heated when ready to use.

title: easy salsa dip
directions: In glass pie plate, spread softened cream cheese.
Next, pour jar of salsa on cream cheese and spread to sides.
Top with olives and cheese, respectively.
Cook in microwave, usually needs approximately 7 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 8 qt. pan, brown chicken over medium high heat. Drain fat. Add 3 qt. water, onion, salt & pepper. Cook chicken until tender, cool and remove from bone. Dough: Cut shortening into flour, add salt, baking powder, eggs, and enough water to make a soft dough. Roll thin on floured surface. Cut into 2 inch squares and add piece by piece to boiling broth, stirring occasionally. Add soup, parsley, and potatoes. Cover and simmer until dough is cooked, about 25 minutes.

title: tandouri chicken(silver bowl winner 1994)
directions: Rinse and dry chicken breasts.
Score each breast two or three times on each side.
Combine other ingredients (except rice) in a bowl.
Note:
Chicken may be allowed to marinate in mixture overnight.
Brush chicken with sauce.
Place on grill or in broiler.
Cook, covered; turning and basting every 5 to 10 minutes until juices run clear.
Serve chicken on rice.

title: rae's banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and bananas; add melted butter and eggs, beaten lightly; then add sour milk, soda, flour and walnuts.
Bake 1 hour slowly at 350°.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: peach puff salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple and Jell-O in saucepan and let come to a boil. Set aside to cool. Mix Cool Whip, buttermilk and pecans. Then mix all ingredients. Put in the refrigerator and let chill overnight.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of double boiler with water hot, beating constantly with hand mixer until peaks form when beaters are raised up.
Especially good on angel food cake.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Mix egg yolks, water and oil together.
Add flavoring and cake mix.
Stir or beat until fluffy.
Bake at 350° until done.
Turn out on wire racks to cool.
I use three (3) 9-inch cake pans.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Drop on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Whip the ingredients gently with a whisk until well combined. Cover loosely and let set at room temperature for three days, stirring daily.
At the end of 3 days, starter should be bubbly when you stir it and have a clean, sour aroma.
The starter is now ready for use.
It may be stored in refrigerator for 14 days.
To replenish after using, add 1 cup flour, 1 cup milk and 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Pick over peas before cleaning and remove any bruised or spotted ones.
Soak in water overnight in a covered pot.
Add diced onion to peas while they are soaking.
The following day, strain and pour off water.
Return peas and onions to pot.
Add celery, garlic, parsley and pickled meat.
Fill pot with water just to cover ingredients.
Cook over a medium flame and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over boiled rice.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water.
Rinse and drain.
Brown meat in butter.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt, then add tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In another dish, combine sour crem, onions and noodles.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of noodle mixture and meat mixture.
Begin with noodles ending with meat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix biscuit mix and sour cream.
Pour in Sprite and mix.
Roll into large ball.
Sprinkle a little biscuit mix on pastry sheet, waxed paper or counter top.
Knead dough 2 or 3 times.
Roll out and cut.
Dip each biscuit in small amount of melted butter and place in pan touching but not too crowded.
Bake about 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Brush with a little more melted butter to serve.

title: baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip fish into lemon juice.
Spray pan with Pam.
Sprinkle with with garlic, chicken bouillon, thyme and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: savory herb casserole bread
directions: Generously grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In a small skillet, cook onion and garlic in margarine or butter until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Pour into big casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup rice, uncooked.
Lay cut up chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups and water together.
Pour on top of chicken and rice.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ice cream churn.

title: chicken cacciatore casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon parsley and remaining ingredients except chicken and cheeses.
Pour over rice. Arrange chicken on top of rice mixture; bake covered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Uncover casserole; sprinkle Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over top and bake 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle remaining parsley over top just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crackle top molasses cookies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda, spices and salt.
Beat butter and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add molasses on low speed.
Add flour mixture; blend well.
Divide dough in half.
Chill dough; form dough by tablespoonfuls into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375° until evenly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute before removing to rack to cool.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 78.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Split
jalapenos
lengthwise
and
remove
seeds.
Mash cream cheese and
add
mayonnaise,
a
small amount at a time, with a mashing and whipping motion until about the consistency of stiff whipped cream.
Stuff peppers and get set for a taste delight.

title: chili lasagna rolls
directions: Spread one side of each noodle with 3 tablespoons chili.
Lay 2 halves of cheese over the chili.
Roll up and place seam side down in a greased baking dish.
Spread remaining chili on top of rolls. Place grated cheese on top.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
To serve:
Top rolls with sour cream and green onion.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Put diced chicken in pan; cover with broth (add some water if needed). Add onion, potatoes and carrots. Cook slowly for 10 minutes. Add English peas, soup, salt and pepper. Place one pie crust in the bottom of a round casserole dish. Put mixture in and cover with the top crust. Dot with butter and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chili burgers(diabetic recipe)
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in a pan. Drain fat, add soup and chili powder. Stir and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: impossible french apple pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix apples and spices; turn into plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour into plate. Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: kids make pudding in a cloud
directions: You will need 6 dessert cups.

title: baked lentils with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish the lentils and the next 8 ingredients.
Cover tightly; bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover and stir in carrots and celery.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in pepper and parsley.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: fresh asparagus(servings: 6)
directions: Wash asparagus spears and trim off tough ends.
Place asparagus in boiling, salted water and cook until tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain off liquid.

title: viola's fancy biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick and sour cream.
Add just enough club soda to moisten.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut with a biscuit cutter. Bake in an oiled pan at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: woodstock
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
You can parboil the green pepper in the bottom part of double boiler while cheese melts.
(Cut pepper in half, remove seeds and boil a few minutes until tender to fork.)
To melted cheese, add mushroom soup, pimiento, cut-up eggs and cut-up pepper.
Serve on toast.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour and cornstarch in double boiler; stir in water.
Cook over medium heat until mixture becomes thick and clear.
Add a little hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Return to mixture and cook a few minutes more.
Remove from heat and blend in lemon juice, rind and butter.
Pour into a baked pie shell. Cool slightly.

title: watkins caramel dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Best with apples, but serve with any fruit.

title: ranch-style chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine onion soup, buttermilk, flour and garlic; set aside.
In lightly greased 2-quart casserole, arrange chicken and vegetables.
Add soup mix and bake, covered, 20 minutes.
Remove cover; top with bread crumbs, combined with butter.
Continue baking, uncovered, 25 minutes.

title: willie b's corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° until golden brown. Can be easily frozen if any leftover.

title: crunchy slaw
directions: Open noodles and remove seasoning packet. Set noodles aside; you will use them later. Mix oil and seasoning packet together. Add sugar, vinegar, onion and broccoli salad. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight (refrigerate long enough for the oil to soak into broccoli salad). Roast almonds and sunflower seeds in oven for 10 minutes. Break up Ramen noodles and mix with nuts. Add to slaw and serve immediately.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425° (220°C).
Generously grease 6 or 9 muffin tins.
In a medium-sized bowl, stir together all ingredients. Pour into greased muffin tins to within 1/4 inch of top of each cup.
Bake 35 minutes or until popped and golden.
Pierce side of each popover, if desired, and return to turned-off oven 10 to 15 minutes to dry.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice tops off tomatoes and discard. Using small knife, remove center pulp from tomatoes, leaving shells intact.
Discard seeds, chop pulp and reserve.
Invert tomato shells onto paper toweling to drain.
Cook sausage, onion and garlic until sausage is browned and crumbly.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in reserved tomato pulp, zucchini, basil, vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice, Provolone and 4 tablespoons Parmesan. Place tomatoes in 2-quart (10 x 13-inch) rectangular baking dish. Spoon filling into shells, mounding on top.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
Serve immediately.

title: mandarin ham salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine ham, pineapple, cherries, oranges and marshmallows.
Mix sour cream, mayo and rice.
Pour sour cream mixture over other ingredients and gently fold everything together. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8 generously.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions (don't drain).
Add Cheez Whiz, rice, chicken, soup, sauteed onion and milk.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 2-quart baking dish.

title: spicy barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a large shallow dish.
Add ribs, cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, turning ribs occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place ribs on grill, bone side down, over slow coals for 30 minutes.
Brush with sauce and cook another 30 minutes, basting and turning frequently. Serves 4 to 6.

title: russian tea
directions: Add
sugar to boiling water after sugar dissolves.
Add tea and
cloves tied in a cloth.
Let stand for 6 or 8 minutes and remove
tea
and
cloves.
Squeeze	juice from lemons and oranges. Strain
and
add
to tea infusion.
This may be made beforehand and reheated when needed.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 375°.

title: sweet potato chips
directions: l. In medium bowl, pour ice water over potatoes to cover; stir in sugar and 1/4 tsp. of the salt. Let stand 30 minutes.

title: harvard beans
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion.
Saute until tender.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Blend vinegar.
Add water and stir into butter and onion until mixture thickens.
Add to heated beans.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easter strawberries
directions: Mix gelatin, nuts and shredded coconut with the Eagle Brand milk.
Shape into strawberries.
Refrigerate until cold (much easier to handle).
Dip the top into green sugar.
Roll the berry in the red sugar.
If desired you can soak slivered almonds in green food coloring and use for stems.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thoroughly.
Cover them with water and add the salt.
Stir.
Let this set in a large container, not aluminum, for 2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together in mixer.

title: gayla's lasagna
directions: Cook
lasagna
noodles	as directed.
Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Combine tomato sauce and seasonings (suit to your taste).
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine all cheeses together. Layer
noodles,
meat
mixture/sauce
and	cheese mixtures. Repeat layers.
Cover with aluminum
foil;	bake 45 minutes in 300° oven.	Serves 6.

title: impossible chicken quiche
directions: In a lightly greased pie plate, layer the first five ingredients.
Put the milk, Bisquick and eggs in a blender.
Beat at high speed for one minute.
Pour over layered mixture.
Bake at 400°, 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken and scallions
directions: Brown chicken in oil and remove.
In same pan saute scallions, garlic and shallot.
Meanwhile, remove tomatoes from can, place in bowl and chop into small chunks.
Add to pan.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add wine, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add chicken, meat side down.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over Fritos or spaghetti topped with grated cheese.

title: little porky
directions: Preheat 12-inch Dutch oven on the bottom for 5 minutes. Place diced
pork
in oven.
Stir until browned.	Add soup and mix in with pork.	Simmer for 45 minutes.	Place mushrooms on top. Prepare
stuffing according to directions.	Place on top of mushrooms.	Bake
minutes
with
coals on top and 5 coals on bottom.

title: maligne lake coffee cake
directions: Trim crusts from top, sides and ends without cutting through bottom crust.
Cut down center of loaf lengthwise, then across, into 10 or 12 cubes, not through.
Cream together margarine or butter, brown sugar and cream.
Spread creamed mixture between, all around and on top of cubes.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cinnamon.
Bake uncovered at 450° for 10 minutes in foil lined bread pan.
May be frozen.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour slowly, while mixing.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring.
Bake at 300° (or 275°).

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Butter glass pie pan.
Peel and slice apples.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon and pour over apples.
Mix butter, flour and brown sugar (will be lumpy).
Pour over apples.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add onions, garlic, sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook 8 ounces of macaroni, then place half of macaroni in casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 meat, 1/2 sour cream and slices of cheese; repeat.
End with slices of Mozzarella.
Cover.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Uncover and let cheese brown.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, chicken, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and chopped jalapeno pepper.
Top half of each tortilla with 1/4 cup soup mixture, spreading evenly to within 1/2 inch of edge. Moisten edges of tortillas with water; fold over, pressing edges to seal.
On 2 large baking sheets, arrange filled tortillas. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Garnish with tomato, jalapeno pepper slices and cilantro, if desired.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
