Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Freezes well.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer beans, chillies, salsa taco mix, sour cream and cheddar cheese in a 9 x13-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool for about 15 minutes. Top with lettuce, tomato, and onion.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
This is most easily done by using your hands.
Roll as for icebox cookies and wrap in wax paper that has been sprinkled with paprika.
When chilled, slice and serve with crackers.
Makes about 40 slices.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 340° for 1 hour.
Makes one large pie.

title: tater crisp chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine potato flakes and salt in plastic bag.
Rinse chicken pieces in cold water, then shake in the plastic bag.
Place chicken, skin side down, in melted butter.
Bake 60 minutes; turn once after 30 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine soup and enchilada sauce.
Grease a large casserole and layer tortillas and meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Repeat layers until all mixture is used.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, 1 stick margarine and potatoes.
Mix corn flake crumbs with remaining margarine.

title: lime ginger chicken
directions: Mix marinade.
Marinate chicken breasts in shallow casserole or plastic pan overnight.
Grill chicken, covered, 4 inches from medium coals for 15 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to flour mixture with Crisco and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Wrap in see-through paper.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: venison chili
directions: Combine venison, ground beef and onion in a Dutch oven.
Cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble beef.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water and chili powder.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until venison is tender, adding more water as needed. Yields about 7 cups.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Precook onion and celery in about one cup of water until tender.
Add onion/celery mixture to all other ingredients. Spray 9 x 12-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour into pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes (just until set).
Serves 12 to 16.

title: mexicanos tacos
directions: In skillet brown beef and cook green pepper until tender; stir to separate meat.
Add soups and cherry peppers.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Fill each taco shell with 3 to 4 tablespoons meat mixture.
Top each with remaining ingredients. Makes 24 tacos.

title: california polka dot bread
directions: Combine raisins and water. Bring to a boil. Cool to room temperature. Mix next 4 ingredients. Stir into raisin mixture. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to mixture, beating well. Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes.

title: hors d'oeuvre(kids even like these)
directions: This is the amount you want to make.
Peel the skin off your tomatoes and add 2 tablespoons sugar to every quart jar.
Add 1 cup of pepper to every quart, any type pepper you like, one medium onion to quart jar and don't forget to salt and pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons of white vinegar to each quart.
Add 1 tablespoon of Zenic in each quart.
If you don't know this spice, just ask for canning chow chow spice; they will know.
Chop tomatoes into any size you desire.
Add pepper, onion and spices.
Do not cook, let sit for a day.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes.
Bring pulp to boiling, press through sieve to remove seeds.
Add skins and sugar mixed with flour, salt, and lemon.
Fill crust and dot with butter.
Add top crust. Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning.
Spoon mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch ovenproof dish.
Spread on sour cream and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with corn chips. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: barbecued ground beef
directions: Melt fat in skillet, add meat and brown slightly.
Add onions, peppers and seasonings.
Cover skillet and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve on split buns (6 to 8).

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Day before using, rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Combine kraut with other ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Add oil, egg and buttermilk; mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy caribbean pork medallions(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cut tenderloin into 1/2-inch thick slices. Place each slice between 2 pieces of plastic wrap. Pound to 1/4-inch thickness. Rub both sides of pork pieces with jerk seasoning. Lightly spray large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over medium heat until hot. Add pork. Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once. Remove from skillet. Keep warm. Stir together pineapple juice, mustard and cornstarch until smooth. Add to skillet. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens slightly. Spoon over pork. Makes 2 servings.

title: sangria
directions: Mix together in a large pitcher all ingredients except sparkling water. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight. Add sparkling water and ice cubes. Serve very cold in balloon-shaped wine glasses.

title: baked beans
directions: Prepare 2 days ahead.
Wash and soak beans overnight.
Change water and refill with water until approximately 1-inch over beans. Add bouillon cubes to water; simmer gently until just tender (approximately 2 hours).
In a separate skillet, saute onion, carrot and celery in 2 tablespoons bacon fat until tender.
Add to beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Next day, in a covered casserole dish, bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Serve hot.
(Make sure there is enough liquid to cover beans.)

title: cuban style black bean soup
directions: Garnish:
minced parsley and cilantro, lemon and lime slices, and chopped hard-boiled egg.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg in small bowl.
Melt shortening and cool.
Add milk to egg, then stir this mixture into dry mixture.
Before completely blended, add shortening and stir enough just to mix ingredients.
Add blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tin to 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: spanish okra
directions: Cook onions in as little water as possible.
Add tomatoes and continue heating until they boil, then add okra and again continue cooking until okra is done, about 10 minutes.
Stir with a spoon, vertically, so that onions stay on bottom.
When the okra is done, add sugar and salt and mix thoroughly.
Warmed over Spanish okra is just as good, if not better than the first time.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Add crackers, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into well buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool 1 hour.
Top with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix milk and water. Add pudding mix. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Layer in 2 1/2-quart dish. Use 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding. Chill thoroughly.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Into a large glass bowl, first place the lettuce.
On top of that put a layer of peas, then onions, green peppers, celery, mayonnaise and cheese.
Toss right before serving.

title: italian hot dogs
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook onion, pepper and garlic until vegetables are tender, stirring often.

title: mexican scrambled eggs
directions: Cook ham, green pepper, onion and chili sauce until tender. Blend in eggs.
Cook over a low heat until eggs are set.
Stir gently now and then.

title: lemon squares ii
directions: Blend butter, sugar and flour for pastry.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs with sugar. Add flour, juice and rind.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into fingers.

title: frosting
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients plus 1/3 of the powdered sugar and part of milk.
Add remaining milk and sugar.
Mix until creamy. (Add more milk to thin.
Add powdered sugar to thicken.)

title: cherry surprise
directions: Spread pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Place pineapple over cherries. Sprinkle sugar over this, then sprinkle cake mix over this.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix. Then put coconut and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Spread 1 can refried beans on serving platter.
Topped with taco meat and salsa.
Spread sour cream evenly.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and black olives.
Arrange tortilla chips along outside of patties.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to boil.
Can be frozen.

title: mom roles' english tea cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and oleo; add eggs.
Add flour, soda and baking powder alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven.
May add nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Mix cheese, vanilla and sugar until blended. Add eggs.
Beat well. Place wafers in cupcake papers in muffin tin; spoon cheese mixture over wafers. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool and spoon favorite pie filling on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together; pour into shell.
Put 1/4 cup Cool Whip on top.
Chill and serve.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Day ahead or up to 3 days ahead:
Into 1-quart saucepan, drain liquid from beets.
Place beets and eggs into 1 1/2-quart jar or large bowl.
Into beet juice in saucepan, stir vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours to allow flavor to penetrate eggs.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, add yolks, buttermilk and shortening.
You may use other shortening.
Beat whites of 3 eggs and fold in dough.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
They can be kept refrigerated unbaked for as long as one week.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except morsels.
Add morsels last (mix again).
Turn into tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: okra patties
directions: Drain okra, mash well.
Add egg and beat.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to okra mixture.
Drop by spoon in hot butter or oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn only once.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, syrup and butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil on high, stirring constantly, until butter is melted.
Remove from stove and gradually add hot syrup to eggs; stir all the while.
Add hickory nuts to mixture and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Combine shortening and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix well.
Add pecans, dates and cherries.
Shape into balls,
roll each ball of dough in corn flakes.
Place on greased
baking
sheet.
Top
each	cookie	with
candied cherry.
Bake in moderate 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tupperware bread
directions: Put in large quart Tupperware bowl.
Set in warm water until lid pops off.
Take out and knead.
Make loaves or rolls; let rise. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° in greased Bundt pan.

title: swiss chicken breast
directions: Spray lightly 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on bottom of pan. Lay Swiss cheese slices over chicken.
Pour 2 cans of soup over chicken.
Lay croutons on top.
Melt butter and pour over top. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Bake slow.)

title: tostada salad
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Mix in refried beans and sour cream.
Lay taco chips on bottom of dish.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top and melt under broiler.
Add salad fixings on top and garnish with hot sauce and cheese.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery together.
Add tomatoes, green beans and seasonings.
Add macaroni and cook slowly.

title: german pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Butter well two 9 inch cake pans. Put eggs into bowl and beat until light yellow in color. Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth. Pour into prepared pans and bake for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes. Slide onto hot plates. Serve with lemon slices, powdered sugar and butter. Syrup, jelly, honey or fruit flavored butters may also be served.

title: lisa's cornbread salad
directions: Cook corn bread mix according to package direction.
Let cool.
Crumble the cornbread and set aside.
Combine veggies and toss.
Mix pickle juice and mayonnaise together.
Mix all ingredients together and chill at least two hours before serving. Serves 10.

title: rocky road ice cream pie
directions: In bowl, mix marshmallow cream with cream; stir in half the raisins
and almonds.
Place 1/2 cup of mixture in a small bowl. Freeze both bowls.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, baking powder, sugar and oil together as for biscuits.
Add dry yeast dissolved in warm water.
Then add buttermilk.
Roll out desired amount.
Cut as for biscuits.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes at 450° on a cookie sheet.

title: mallie's applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling point.
Add lime gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in ginger ale and orange rind.
Pour into 1 quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.

title: hanky panky appetizer
directions: Brown meats together and drain thoroughly.
Turn off heat; add all other ingredients, stir to melt cheese.
Refrigerate for later use or use immediately for appetizers.
Spread on slices of bread and place on cookie sheets.
Broil on low 10 minutes or less on top rack.
Serve immediately, while hot.

title: anytime casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs.
In skillet brown meat with onion, salt, pepper and green pepper.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.
Then, on medium heat, stir into meat mixture the catsup, steak sauce and tomatoes.
Cook 3 minutes on medium heat. Drain macaroni and add to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove; add cheese on top.
Put back in oven for 1 minute longer.
Serves 6 people.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and pudding. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix. Add flour and baking soda. Fold in chips and nuts. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Mix cornbread mix.
Put half of cornbread mix in greased casserole dish.
Put meat mixture in on top of cornbread mix.
Add cheese and rest of cornbread mix. Bake for 30 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: southern style pecan pie
directions: Beat together first five ingredients.
Add pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.

title: friendship tea mix(great gift for friends)
directions: In a medium container, combine instant tea, lemonade drink mix, orange drink mix, cinnamon, cloves and cinnamon candies.
Mix well; store mixture in an airtight container.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: In a small bowl combine chicken, soy sauce and vegetable oil. Place broccoli and 1/2 cup chicken broth in wok.
Cook with medium heat until stems are tender.
Push up the side of wok.
Increase heat to high.
Add chicken mixture and garlic powder.
Stir-fry until chicken turns white and is cooked.
Combine cornstarch with remaining 1/2 of broth.
Stir into wok and heat until thickened. Serve over bed of rice and sprinkle with chow mein noodles.

title: heavenly banana pudding(low-fat)
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in large bowl in this order:
vanilla wafers, bananas, Cool Whip/pudding mixture.
Repeat.
Crumble wafers on last layer of pudding mixture.
This is low-fat and delicious.

title: mildred's pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Spread pineapple in oleo coated casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Spread cheese over flour-sugar mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers over cheese. Cut oleo into small pieces; dot over Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Good with ham or venison.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken. Dip each piece of chicken in sauce. Place skin side up in a single layer in a shallow baking pan. Pour in remaining sauce. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: cake topped blueberry dessert
directions: Place the blueberries in a greased 8-inch square pan.
In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar, milk, and butter until smooth. Pour over blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack. 6-8 servings.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in food processor to blend. Keep refrigerated.

title: black forest parfaits
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using skim milk. Divide half of pudding evenly among 6 (6-ounce) parfait or stemmed glasses. Spoon half of pie filling evenly over pudding in glasses. Top parfaits evenly with half of cookie crumbs. Repeat layers with remaining pudding, pie filling and cookie crumbs. Top each serving with 1 tablespoon whipped topping and garnish with fresh cherries, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add syrup and mix together.
Add pecans.
Bake in unbaked 10-inch pie shell at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
In bacon drippings, add onion and parsley and cook until tender.
Transfer to a 3-quart casserole dish; add crumbled bacon and remaining ingredients, except cheese. Mix well.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be served over cooked rice.
Also, seasonings can be increased if you desire spicier food.

title: cheesecake
directions: Whip cream with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Mix the softened cream cheese with 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Fold in heavy cream.

title: orange balls
directions: Melt oleo and work into crumbs with sugar and vanilla wafers. Add orange juice.
Make into small balls.
You can do this different ways.
I like best to put ground or chopped nuts inside balls and roll in coconut.
Can freeze on cookie sheet, then put in plastic bags for freezer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, Jell-O, sugar and water.
Cook until thickened. Remove from heat and add about 3 caps of red food coloring.
Let mixture cool before pouring into baked pie shell lined with fresh, sliced strawberries.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal and toss to coat evenly.
Sprinkle powdered sugar all over, tossing to coat all sides.
Let coating dry before storing in an airtight container.

title: stuffing for chicken, etc.
directions: Rub margarine into breadcrumbs.
Add herbs, lemon rind, mushrooms and seasoning and bind with beaten egg.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add strawberries (do not have to be thawed).
Stir, let set until jelly consistency.
Fold in can milk (which has been whipped); also fold in cake which has been broken or cut in pieces.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan or torte pan; chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin, waters, sugar and salt.
Set until firm. Add cranberries, nuts and celery.
Mix together and refrigerate.

title: special sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, just until top is crusty and casserole is hot all the way through.

title: cheese snack
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with cheese.
Beat eggs and mix with picante sauce.
Pour over cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: stuffed hot vienna bread
directions: Melt lemon juice, margarine, poppy seed, dry mustard and chopped onion.
Mix mushrooms and Swiss cheese.
Cut bread part way through and stuff mushroom/cheese mixture between.
Pour melted butter mixture between bread cuts.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta with shrimp
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and saute garlic about one minute. Add peppers, basil, shrimp and tomatoes with juice.
Cook until shrimp are done (about 3 minutes).
Pour over cooked pasta and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Toss well and serve immediately.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot and saute onions, green pepper, carrots, celery and garlic until onions are translucent.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: toffee chip cookies
directions: Cream oil, oleo, sugars, vanilla.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add dry ingredients mixed together.
Then cereals, coconut, pecans and chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake 350 for 12 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute on cookie sheet, transfer to rack to cool.
Makes 12 dozen.
Can be halved.

title: tuna salad delight
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Mix together the mayonnaise and lemon juice and add to the other ingredients.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all together; form into small balls.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix grated Cheddar and American cheese into rest of ingredients.
Pour all into casserole dish.
Cook 1/2 bag medium egg noodles and drain.
Mix in with rest.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Place pork chops in a deep dish baking pan.
Top each one with an onion ring and bell pepper ring.
Blend remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over chops and bake in a 350° oven until pork chops are done through.
Chops should be covered while cooking.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Delicious served warm.

title: yogurt and cucumber dip
directions: Mash garlic with olive oil.
Add to yogurt.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and make it into a ball.
Put in plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: In a bowl, cream together butter, sugar and eggs until very creamy and well blended. Add salt. Stir in flour, mixing to blend well. Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan.
Cut into squares. Garnish with powdered sugar or pecan halves, if desired.

title: peanut butter cookie dream
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla; add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine everything except carrots.
Cook carrots and while still hot, add to sauce.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: brandy homemade southern style
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Dissolve yeast in water. Let cool.
Add cool water to crushed fruit and chopped lemons. Stir every day for 7 days.
Add raisins and let stand for 21 days. Do not stir for 21 days.

title: egg rolls
directions: Stir-fry cabbage, Chinese vegetables, bean sprouts, carrots and green onion until crisp, not well done.
Mix with meat chopped fine (or ground).
Place small amount in egg roll center.
Fold over, sealing sides with cornstarch paste.
Seal loose ends.
Deep fry.

title: pineapple gooey cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, juice and eggs.
Grease and flour long pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: english brown stew
directions: Flour
meat
and brown in a little hot fat.
Add water, onion, seasonings
and
tomato juice.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours. Add vegetables and cook until done, about 1/2 hour.

title: oven french fries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Peel and cut potatoes like French fries. Put margarine on flat cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet in oven for 3 minutes to melt margarine.
Put potatoes on cookie sheet. Toss to coat with margarine.
Bake approximately 1 hour, turning potatoes every 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rice-oat pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop onto oiled skillet. Cook until golden brown on each side.

title: candied nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together egg white and water, then beat until frothy.
Dip nuts in egg mixture, then cover with cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: popovers
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Spray muffin tins with Pam. Pour into tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12.
Serve with jam.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Simmer blackberries, 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup sugar for 15 minutes on medium heat in saucepan.
In bowl, add flour, Wesson oil and ice water.
Then work into a bowl in middle of the flour and knead until all mixed together. Separate 1/2 the dough and roll out 1 portion of dough flat and cut in thin strips.
Pour 1/2 blackberries in glass dish.
Cover with 1/2 dough strips.
Pour remaining blackberries over dough strips.
Add remaining dough strips.
Pour 1 cup sugar over dough strips.
Slice remaining 1/2 stick butter and dot on dough strips. Cook 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar in 1/2 cup warm water; allow to stand 45 minutes.

title: ellen's black-eyed pea soup
directions: Remove debris, wash and cook peas according to package directions.
Save cooking water for soup liquid.
Remove fat from pork chops.
Render fat in olive oil.
Remove pieces of fat.
Add vegetables and saute until tender.
Add vegetables, whole pork chops and remaining ingredients to beans.
Add additional water or broth to desired consistency.
Cook on low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender and tasty.
Can also be cooked for 8 to 10 hours in crock-pot on low temperature.
Remove meat and cut into small pieces before serving.
If you use less liquid, this can also be served as a side dish.

title: skillet steaks with onion gravy
directions: Measure broth in a large measuring cup. Whisk in ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper. Set aside. Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Add steaks; cook for about 4 minutes on each side on medium. Remove steaks from skillet; cover and keep warm. Pour off fat from skillet. Thinly slice onions; add butter to skillet and melt over medium heat. Add onion; cook stirring continually, about 3 minutes. Cover, reduce heat to medium low; cook about 5 minutes longer. Stir broth mixture into skillet; cook until heated through, about 2 minutes. Pour over steaks. Serve immediately.

title: aunt lill's scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place a layer of potatoes in baking dish and top with some onion.
Sift a little flour over this layer.
Add 2 more layers.
Don't put flour on top layer.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Add a bit of salt and pepper.
Add water until you can see it on the side of the dish.
Cover and bake about an hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake it a little longer.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar. Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Do not overbake.)
Press chocolate kiss in center of each ball immediately after baking.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni in salted
water
according
to	package directions.
Save a little of
the cooking water when draining macaroni.
Grate both cheeses.
Put
half of the grated cheese in drained macaroni; stir and let it melt.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Gently stir all ingredients together, then press and spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place butter, milk and sugar in pot; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add to boiled mixture the peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff, flour and walnuts; stir well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain tomatoes.
Keep juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add tomatoes, liquid, rice and taco mix to meat.
Simmer about 25 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking occasionally.
Before you serve, melt cheese on top and then lettuce on top.
You can also crumble tacos and put on top.

title: plain pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until pieces are the size of a small pea.
Gently and slowly mix in ice water.
Form into a ball and divide.
Flatten on floured surface.
Roll from center to edge until 1/8-inch thick. Trim crust 1/2-inch beyond plate and flute.
Vent and bake according to recipe.
Yield:
Two 8 or 9-inch pie crusts.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in 1/2-inch hot fat.
Place a fried tortilla on a plate.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and chopped onion.
Cover with chili sauce.
Place another tortillas on top.
Repeat with cheese and onion.
Pour chili sauce over top.
Three layers may be used if desired.
A fried egg may be served on top.
Bake in preheated gas oven at 350° until cheese melts and enchiladas are hot.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Mix sugar and flour.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well (batter will be thin).
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan until middle is done.

title: easy mashed potatoes
directions: Pour butter and milk over potatoes.
Mash.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix with cream cheese.
Bake covered for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add fajita spices to taste.
Heat beans.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Put flour tortillas in ovenproof bowl and fold edges upwards.
Put small ball of foil in center of tortilla to hold it down, if necessary.
Heat tortillas for 10 minutes or until crisp.
Layer in tortillas in this order:
meat, beans, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and sour cream.
Top with salad dressing of choice.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Mix the corn oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, then add the pecans and apples.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in rectangular pan.
While still hot, stick holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over entire cake.
Let cake cool and then spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut over the top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot-almond antarctica
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Cover bottom of pan with 1/3 of the crumb mixture.
Spread 1/2 of the ice cream over crumbs.
Spread 1/2 of the jam over ice cream.
Repeat layers, using next 1/3 of the crumbs and remaining ice cream and jam.
Top with last 1/3 of crumbs.
Freeze.
Cut into squares. Garnish each serving with a fresh mint leaf.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: wonderful easy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake for 350 degrees for 7 to 9 minutes. This recipe works great with different cake mixes and different chips, like butter flavor cake mix with butter brickle bits or broken bits of Butterfinger bars.

title: auntie's lemon pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except lemon juice in top of double boiler until it begins to thicken.
Add lemon juice and cook a little longer.
Cool before pouring into baked pie shell.
Top with stiffly beaten egg whites and brown in 350° oven.

title: hot spice tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep in a sealed jar.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, salt and sugar to a boil.
Add tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Cook over medium heat until tomatoes can be pierced with a toothpick easily.
Put in hot, clean jars and seal immediately.

title: vegetable quesadilla combination
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until barely tender.
Add mushrooms and saute until mushrooms just start to darken as they absorb the butter.
Mix in salt and set aside.
Combine Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Place 4 tortillas on lightly buttered or oiled rectangular pancake griddle; let them warm through (you can tell by just touching them lightly with your finger), then turn each one over.
Top the 4 tortillas with the filling mixture as follows:
First, half of the cheese, vegetable mixture, bacon, pimientos and sliced ripe olives (optional), then the remaining cheese.
Put another tortilla on top of each.
Cook until bottom starts to brown and cheese starts to melt.

title: melt in your mouth quick chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Blend soup with stock.
Pour over chicken.
Combine flour, buttermilk and butter; mix well.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour; or until crust rises to top and is golden brown.

title: marvelous cheese straws
directions: Sift flour.
Pour melted butter over grated cheese.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Work it together using hands until it forms a good ball.
Press through a cookie press on ungreased cookie sheets.
Cut across in 3 in. strips before cooking.
Bake 20 minutes at 325-350° until they stop sizzling.
Do not brown, but bottoms should be golden.

title: kris' calico beans
directions: Cook ground beef and bacon together until browned.
Drain off excess fat;
save a few tablespoons to put in mixture.
Mix together ground beef and bacon with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper and butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at 100% power for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour and gradually add milk. Microwave at 100% for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes or until boiling and thickened, stirring twice.
Add a little hot mixture to yolks and blend well.
Return to casserole.
Add seasonings.
Stir in 1/2 of cheese and crabmeat.
Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave at 100% power for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through, stirring twice. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of casserole.
Microwave at 100% power for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: gourmet caesar chicken
directions: *Follow directions on Good Seasons package and cruet.

title: double delicious bars
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Then pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips and press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brown.
Cool and cut.

title: jalapeno sourdough bread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except vinegar and jalapeno peppers, kneading
thoroughly.
Cover and allow to rise for 30 to 45
minutes.
Knead
in vinegar and chopped peppers.
Allow to rise for
another hour or so.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat the oil in a large frying pan.
Add the onion and fry until golden.
Add garlic and peppers.
Add eggplant, zucchini and tomatoes.
Fry vegetables gently, then cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mae shea's red chicken
directions: Wash and cut chicken into serving size pieces.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Add catsup, minced garlic and chopped onion.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is very tender and gravy is thick.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Serve over cooked rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add sour cream, flour and baking soda; mix well.
Add vanilla and poppy seed. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
